<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	The factors discussed in Part I, Item 1A. &#x201C;Risk Factors&#x201D;
</FONT>
</P>
</TD>
</TR>

<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">

	PART

<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	I

<EFX_BUSINESS>
<A NAME="FIS_BUSINESS"></A>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	Item&nbsp;1. Busines
</FONT>
<A NAME="ADPT-20151231X10K_HTM_ITEM1BUSINESS_762321">
</A>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	s
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	We are a patient-centered healthcare organization providing emergency medical care through the largest network of independent freestanding emergency rooms in the United States and partnerships with leading healthcare systems.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	We have experienced rapid growth in recent periods, growing from 14 freestanding facilities at the end of 2012 to 81 freestanding facilities and two fully licensed general hospitals as of December 31,&nbsp;2015.&nbsp;&nbsp;We currently own or operate facilities located in the (i) Houston, Dallas/Fort Worth, San Antonio and Austin, Texas markets; (ii) Colorado Springs and Denver, Colorado markets; and (iii) Phoenix, Arizona market
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	. In the Arizona and Dallas/Fort Worth markets, each of our freestanding facilities are outpatient departments of our hospitals in that market. Each
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	facility opened in 2015 was newly constructed.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
</FONT>
</P>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="MARGIN-LEFT:10.2941176470588%;MARGIN-RIGHT:10.2941176470588%;">
<P>
<FONT SIZE="1">
</FONT>
</P>
<DIV STYLE="WIDTH:100%">
<P STYLE="MARGIN:24PT 0PT 0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:CENTER;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	4
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
</FONT>
</P>
</DIV>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="MARGIN-LEFT:10.2941176470588%;MARGIN-RIGHT:10.2941176470588%;">
<HR ALIGN="CENTER" STYLE='BACKGROUND-COLOR:#000000; BORDER-WIDTH:0; COLOR:#000000; HEIGHT:2PT; LINEHEIGHT:0; WIDTH:100%;'>
</HR>
<P STYLE="PAGE-BREAK-AFTER:ALWAYS">
	&nbsp;
</P>
<A NAME="eolPage5"></A>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="MARGIN-LEFT:10.2941176470588%;MARGIN-RIGHT:10.2941176470588%;">
<DIV STYLE="WIDTH:100%">
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 6PT;COLOR:#0563C1;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<A HREF="#ADPT-20151231X10K_HTM_TOC">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#0563C1;">
	Table of Contents
</FONT>
</A>
</P>
</DIV>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="MARGIN-LEFT:10.2941176470588%;MARGIN-RIGHT:10.2941176470588%;">
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	Since our founding in 2002, our mission has been to address the need within our local communities for immediate and convenient access to quality emergency care in a patient
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209;friendly, cost
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209;effective setting. We believe we are transforming the emergency care experience with a differentiated and convenient care delivery model which improves access, reduces wait times and provides high
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209;quality clinical and diagnostic services on
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209;site. Our facilities are fully licensed and provide comprehensive, emergency care with an acuity mix that we believe is comparable to hospital
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209;based emergency rooms.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	Emergency care is a significantly underserved market in the United States today and the current system is overburdened.
</FONT>
</P>
<DIV STYLE="WIDTH:100%">
<TABLE STYLE="WIDTH:100%;" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0">
<TR>
<TD STYLE="WIDTH:36PT;">
<P STYLE="WIDTH:36PT;FONT-SIZE:0PT;">
</P>
</TD>
<TD VALIGN="TOP" ALIGN="LEFT" STYLE="WIDTH: 17.00PT; DISPLAY: INLINE;">
<P STYLE="BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;">
<FONT STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;FONT-FAMILY:SYMBOL;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-SIZE:10PT;;">
	&#xB7;
</FONT>
</P>
</TD>
<TD STYLE="WIDTH:1PT;">
<P STYLE="WIDTH:1PT;WIDTH:1PT;FONT-SIZE:0PT;">
</P>
</TD>
<TD ALIGN="LEFT" VALIGN="TOP">
<P STYLE="BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	Demand has grown dramatically, with emergency room&nbsp;visits increasing 47.1%, from 90.8&nbsp;million in 1992 to 133.6&nbsp;million in 2013, while the number of emergency room departments decreased by 11.8% over the same period, from approximately 5,035 in 1992 to approximately 4,440 in 2013, according to the American Hospital Association, or AHA.
</FONT>
</P>
</TD>
</TR>
</TABLE>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="WIDTH:100%">
<TABLE STYLE="WIDTH:100%;" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0">
<TR>
<TD STYLE="WIDTH:36PT;">
<P STYLE="WIDTH:36PT;FONT-SIZE:0PT;">
</P>
</TD>
<TD VALIGN="TOP" ALIGN="LEFT" STYLE="WIDTH: 17.00PT; DISPLAY: INLINE;">
<P STYLE="BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;">
<FONT STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;FONT-FAMILY:SYMBOL;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-SIZE:10PT;;">
	&#xB7;
</FONT>
</P>
</TD>
<TD STYLE="WIDTH:1PT;">
<P STYLE="WIDTH:1PT;WIDTH:1PT;FONT-SIZE:0PT;">
</P>
</TD>
<TD ALIGN="LEFT" VALIGN="TOP">
<P STYLE="BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	In their 2014 National Report Card on America&#x2019;s emergency care environment, the American College of Emergency Physicians, or ACEP, assigned an overall grade of &#x201C;D
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	&#8209;&#x201D; for the category of access to emergency care in the U.S, reflecting too few emergency departments to meet the needs of a growing, aging population and the projected increase in the number of insured individuals as a result of the Patient Protection and Affordable Care Act, as amended by the Health Care and Education Affordability Reconciliation Act of 2010, or the PPACA.
</FONT>
</P>
</TD>
</TR>
</TABLE>
</DIV>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	We believe freestanding emergency rooms are an essential part of the solution, providing access to quality care and offering a significantly improved patient experience relative to traditional hospital emergency departments.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	What We Do and Why We Are Different
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	We focus on providing emergency care through our freestanding emergency rooms with the goal of improving the quality of care and enhancing the overall experience for patients and physicians. We have developed an innovative facility design and infrastructure specifically tailored to the emergency care delivery system that combines staff, equipment and physical layout to deliver high
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209;quality, cost
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209;effective coordinated patient
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209;focused care. This approach limits the need to move patients and provides ease of access to all necessary medical services we provide, allowing us to enhance the overall experience of the patient. Our facility design also allows physicians and nursing staff to provide all levels of care required for our patients during their visit. Our philosophy is to center care around the patient, rather than expect the patient to adapt to our facilities and staff. We believe our focused approach increases patient, physician and staff satisfaction. Innovative characteristics of our emergency facilities include:
</FONT>
</P>
<DIV STYLE="WIDTH:100%">
<TABLE STYLE="WIDTH:100%;" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0">
<TR>
<TD STYLE="WIDTH:36PT;">
<P STYLE="WIDTH:36PT;FONT-SIZE:0PT;">
</P>
</TD>
<TD VALIGN="TOP" ALIGN="LEFT" STYLE="WIDTH: 17.00PT; DISPLAY: INLINE;">
<P STYLE="BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;">
<FONT STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;FONT-FAMILY:SYMBOL;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-SIZE:10PT;;">
	&#xB7;
</FONT>
</P>
</TD>
<TD STYLE="WIDTH:1PT;">
<P STYLE="WIDTH:1PT;WIDTH:1PT;FONT-SIZE:0PT;">
</P>
</TD>
<TD ALIGN="LEFT" VALIGN="TOP">
<P STYLE="BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;COLOR:#000000;">
	24&nbsp;/&nbsp;7 Emergency Care.&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	Freestanding emergency room facilities, which typically range from approximately 6,000 to 7,000 square feet and are located in a convenient, local community setting and open 24&nbsp;hours a day, seven days a week with on
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	&#8209;site emergency staff, including a physician, at all times;
</FONT>
</P>
</TD>
</TR>
</TABLE>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="WIDTH:100%">

</P>

<P STYLE="BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;">
<FONT STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;FONT-FAMILY:SYMBOL;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-SIZE:10PT;;">

<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;COLOR:#000000;">
	Board
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;COLOR:#000000;">
	&#8209;Certified Physicians.&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">

</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	&#8209;certified physicians with an average of 15 years of medical experience who have treated more than 600,000 patients at our facilities;

<TR>
<TD STYLE="WIDTH:36PT;">
<P STYLE="WIDTH:36PT;FONT-SIZE:0PT;">
</P>
</TD>
<TD VALIGN="TOP" ALIGN="LEFT" STYLE="WIDTH: 17.00PT; DISPLAY: INLINE;">
<P STYLE="BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;">

<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;COLOR:#000000;">

</FONT>
</P>
</TD>
</TR>
</TABLE>
</DIV>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	We operate at the higher end of the acuity and emergency care spectrum. Our capabilities and offerings differ from other care models as outlined below:
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;TEXT-ALIGN:CENTER;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	Spectrum of Primary and Emergency Care Services
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 4PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	Market Opportunity
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 4PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	Freestanding emergency rooms remain the least penetrated alternate site provider segment in the U.S. healthcare sector. As of 2015, there were approximately 500 freestanding emergency rooms in the United States as compared to approximately 2,800 retail clinics, 5,500 ambulatory surgery centers and 10,000 urgent care centers. We believe this represents a significant opportunity to deliver quality care in the freestanding emergency room setting and transform this underpenetrated market. We have developed a highly scalable business model for establishing new freestanding emergency rooms that include attractive unit economics, sophisticated data analytics to support our site
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209;selection process, proven real estate development practices and innovative marketing programs. Using this model, we have grown to become more than three times the size of our next largest independent freestanding emergency room competitor and are expanding rapidly. We seek to transform the emergency care delivery model by offering high
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209;quality, efficient and consumer
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209;oriented healthcare in our local communities.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 4PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	In their 2014 National Report Card on America&#x2019;s emergency care environment, ACEP assigned an overall grade of &#x201C;D
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209;&#x201D; for the category of access to emergency care, reflecting too few emergency departments to meet the needs of a growing, aging population and the projected increase in the number of insured individuals as a result of the PPACA. We believe freestanding emergency rooms are an essential part of the solution.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 4PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	We also believe that we offer a dramatically improved patient experience relative to traditional hospital emergency departments by significantly reducing wait times and providing rapid access to Board
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209;certified physicians on
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209;site. We also provide convenient access to critical, high
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209;acuity care as compared with urgent care centers and are open 24&nbsp;hours a day, seven days a week. Based on patient feedback collected by Press Ganey, First Choice Emergency Room received the prestigious Guardian of Excellence Award in 2013, 2014 and 2015 for exceeding the 95th&nbsp;percentile in patient satisfaction nationwide.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	Industry Trends
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	The emergency room remains a critical access point for millions of Americans who experience sudden serious illness or
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	injury in the United States each year. The availability of that care is under pressure and threatened by a wide range of factors, including shrinking capacity and an increasing demand for services. According to AHA, from 1993 to 2013, the number of emergency room&nbsp;visits increased by 44.3%, while the number of emergency departments decreased by 11.2%.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	We believe freestanding emergency rooms are an essential part of the solution, providing access to high
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209;quality emergency care and offering a significantly improved patient experience relative to traditional hospital emergency departments.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
</FONT>
</P>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="MARGIN-LEFT:10.2941176470588%;MARGIN-RIGHT:10.2941176470588%;">
<P>
<FONT SIZE="1">
</FONT>
</P>
<DIV STYLE="WIDTH:100%">
<P STYLE="MARGIN:24PT 0PT 0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:CENTER;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	6
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">

<DIV STYLE="WIDTH:100%">
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 6PT;COLOR:#0563C1;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<A HREF="#ADPT-20151231X10K_HTM_TOC">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#0563C1;">
	Table of Contents
</FONT>
</A>
</P>
</DIV>

<DIV STYLE="MARGIN-LEFT:10.2941176470588%;MARGIN-RIGHT:10.2941176470588%;">
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	The chart below sets forth the number of emergency departments and emergency department visits from 1992 to 2012 according to AHA:
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;TEXT-ALIGN:CENTER;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
<IMG SRC="http://content.edgar-online.com/edgar_conv_img/2016/02/29/0001558370-16-003672_ADPT20151231X10K001.JPG" STYLE="WIDTH: 6.229167IN; HEIGHT: 3.125IN" ALT="PICTURE 1">
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:CENTER;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	The number of emergency room&nbsp;visits exceeded 136&nbsp;million in 2014, or approximately 259 visits per minute, and care previously provided in inpatient settings is now increasingly being provided in emergency departments. Factors affecting access to emergency care include availability of emergency departments, capacity of emergency departments, and availability of staffing in emergency departments. As the largest operator of freestanding emergency rooms, we offer a solution that addresses the following trends currently affecting the healthcare services market:
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	Poor Access to Emergency Care Including a Shortage of Emergency Rooms
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	According to ACEP, between 1997 and 2007, emergency visit rates increased at two times the rate of growth of the U.S. population, causing a shortage of emergency rooms and persistent emergency department overcrowding with expanding wait times. This emergency room shortage is making it increasingly challenging to meet the rising demand for emergency care. According to ACEP&#x2019;s National Report Card on America&#x2019;s emergency care environment, only 4.2% of active physicians are emergency room physicians, yet they are responsible for 28% of all acute care visits and 11% of all outpatient care in the United States. The shortage of emergency rooms has created an acute need for more access and convenient emergency room care.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	Emergence of Innovative Care Delivery Settings and Access Points
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	Healthcare industry trends, including the increasing demand for care, an aging population and the projected increase in the number of people now insured as a result of PPACA, combined with a shortage of access points, is driving the emergence of innovative care delivery models to meet patient needs for emergency care. Increasing demand for emergency care necessitates new healthcare access points such as freestanding emergency rooms for patients to receive timely and high
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209;quality care. The emergence of freestanding emergency rooms will fill a public need in underserved markets and provide connectivity across the patient care continuum from patient referrals to post
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209;emergency care. Freestanding emergency rooms remain the least penetrated alternate site segment with strong unit growth. This growth is expected to shift the delivery of healthcare services away from traditional inpatient hospitals to more effective and convenient solutions, such as freestanding emergency rooms and other alternate
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209;site settings such as urgent care centers and primary care access points.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
</FONT>
</P>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="MARGIN-LEFT:10.2941176470588%;MARGIN-RIGHT:10.2941176470588%;">
<P>
<FONT SIZE="1">
</FONT>
</P>
<DIV STYLE="WIDTH:100%">
<P STYLE="MARGIN:24PT 0PT 0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:CENTER;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">

	7

<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">

<DIV STYLE="MARGIN-LEFT:10.2941176470588%;MARGIN-RIGHT:10.2941176470588%;">
<DIV STYLE="WIDTH:100%">
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 6PT;COLOR:#0563C1;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<A HREF="#ADPT-20151231X10K_HTM_TOC">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#0563C1;">
	Table of Contents
</FONT>
</A>
</P>
</DIV>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="MARGIN-LEFT:10.2941176470588%;MARGIN-RIGHT:10.2941176470588%;">
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	Increasing Healthcare Consumerism
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	We believe patients will increasingly seek high
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209;quality and efficient care in cost
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209;effective settings. As self
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209;insured employers look to reduce their overall healthcare costs, they are rapidly shifting financial responsibility to patients through higher co
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209;payments and deductibles. These changes to health plan design, coupled with increased pricing transparency, are encouraging patients to take more control of their healthcare spending and seek out more cost
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209;effective and efficient options for their healthcare consumption. As consumers take on a larger share of their healthcare costs and spend more on healthcare services, they want a greater say in how and where they receive care, demanding higher quality care, increased convenience and more service for their dollars spent. This trend of increasing consumerism will benefit freestanding emergency room operators as they offer attractive and convenient neighborhood
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209;based, physician
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209;focused care at significantly reduced wait times. We believe that, given the choice, consumers will choose freestanding emergency rooms for both their convenience and high
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209;quality care and outcomes.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	Opportunities Created by Healthcare Legislation
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	The expected increase in the number of people now insured as a result of PPACA may put additional pressure on an already overburdened emergency room system that lacks capacity and access points. This expected influx of newly insured patients creates opportunities for providers of emergency care with attractive and convenient locations capable of delivering high
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209;quality care. Additionally, we expect PPACA to create greater opportunities for cost
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209;effective providers of healthcare services as healthcare reform activities are expected to promote the transition from traditional fee
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209;for
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209;service payment models to more &#x201C;at risk&#x201D; or &#x201C;capitated&#x201D; models in which providers receive a flat fee per member per month from payors, regardless of the cost of care. These changes will be reflected through the creation of accountable care organizations or other payment model reforms. We believe this shift will create financial incentives to transition many types of medical procedures out of the hospital and into more convenient settings such as freestanding emergency rooms.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	Our Value Proposition
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	Value Proposition for Patients
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	As healthcare has evolved, the consumer has taken greater control of healthcare expenditures and demands more convenient access to healthcare, better value and an improved overall patient experience. Our philosophy is to center care around the patient, rather than expect the patient to adapt to our facilities and staff. We offer patients an attractive value proposition:
</FONT>
</P>
<DIV STYLE="WIDTH:100%">

<P STYLE="BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;">
<FONT STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;FONT-FAMILY:SYMBOL;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-SIZE:10PT;;">

<DIV STYLE="MARGIN-LEFT:10.2941176470588%;MARGIN-RIGHT:10.2941176470588%;">
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	As a result, based on patient feedback collected by Press Ganey, First Choice Emergency Room received the prestigious Guardian of Excellence Award in 2013, 2014 and 2015 for exceeding the 95th&nbsp;percentile in patient satisfaction nationwide.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	Value Proposition for Communities
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	Community providers, including physician&#x2019;s offices and hospital emergency rooms, serve a critical and valuable purpose in delivering healthcare. However, the shortage of emergency rooms makes it increasingly challenging to meet the rising demand for emergency care. This has led to an overburdened emergency room network that is often poorly aligned with care consumption trends.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 8PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	We seek to transform the emergency delivery model and fill a public need by offering high
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209;quality, efficient and consumer
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209;oriented healthcare in our local communities. We offer communities an attractive value proposition:
</FONT>
</P>

</P>
</TD>
<TD VALIGN="TOP" ALIGN="LEFT" STYLE="WIDTH: 17.00PT; DISPLAY: INLINE;">
<P STYLE="BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;MARGIN:0PT 0PT 8PT;">

</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	&#8209;defined compensation program. Payment of malpractice insurance coverage premiums for physicians practicing at our facilities.
</FONT>
</P>

</DIV>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 8PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	Value Proposition for Payors
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 8PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	We believe that our emergency room facilities reduce overall costs for payors by reducing unnecessary tests and patient admittances. According to the National Hospital Ambulatory Medical Care Survey, the national average emergency room inpatient admittance rate was approximately 11.9% in 2011, while our average inpatient admittance rate was approximately 3.8% for the year ended December&nbsp;31, 2015. We believe our facilities provide comprehensive emergency care with an acuity mix that is comparable to hospital
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209;based emergency rooms.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 8PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	Value Proposition for Hospitals
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 8PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	We have an attractive business model that provides communities direct access to emergency care, helping to relieve the overburdened hospital emergency room system. Our
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	freestanding
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	facilities provide high
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209;quality emergency care for a wide variety of conditions, including heart attacks, severe abdominal pain and respiratory distress similar to the care provided in traditional hospital emergency rooms. When hospital
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209;based services such as surgery or cardiac catheterization are needed, patients are stabilized at our facilities before being transferred to nearby hospitals via ambulance. Transfer agreements are in place with local hospitals that often facilitate direct admission.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 8PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">

<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 8PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	Competitive Strengths
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 8PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	We believe the following strengths differentiate us from our competitors and will enable us to capitalize on favorable industry dynamics:
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 8PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	Leader in the Rapidly Expanding Freestanding Emergency Room Market
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	We ar
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	e the largest freestanding emergency room
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	operato
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	r in the United States with 81 freestanding facilities as of December 31,&nbsp;2015, of which
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	, 26 and 29 were opened in 2015 and 2014, respectively.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	We are more than three times the size of our next largest independent freestanding emergency room competitor. We believe our innovative facility model enables us to offer our customers comprehensive emergency services with individualized attention and local convenience. We believe that our scale and scope, when combined with our comprehensive service offerings and tailored best practices, differentiate us from our local and regional competitors. Given our market positions in the highly fragmented and rapidly expanding markets in which we provide our services, we believe there continue to be opportunities to build more facilities in existing and new markets as well as develop new alliances with health systems seeking to enhance their local community presence. This will result in further expanding our leadership in the freestanding emergency room market.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	Superior Patient Experience
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	We strive to consistently offer a superior patient experience through both our medical staff and facility capabilities. Our emergency rooms are staffed with Board
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209;certified physicians and emergency
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209;trained registered nurses capable of handling all emergency room issues with a physician on
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209;site at all times. Each of our
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	freestanding
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	facilities is equipped with a full radiology suite, including CT scanners, digital x
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209;ray and ultrasound, as well as on
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209;site laboratories certified by CLIA and accredited by COLA. Our patients are typically face
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209;to
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209;face with a medical professional within minutes of arrival, and our patient satisfaction ratings exceed the vast majority of hospital emergency rooms nationally. Based on patient feedback collected by Press Ganey, we exceeded the 95th&nbsp;percentile in the nation for patient satisfaction and received the Guardian of Excellence Award in 2013, 2014 and 2015, the highest award bestowed by the organization.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	Scalable Service Model Well
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	&#8209;Positioned for Growth

<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	We maintain the highest standards of clinical excellence, led by our 606 contracted Board
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209;certified physicians who have an average of 15 years of medical experience. We have standardized, highly scalable clinical and operational infrastructure that we believe will support significant continued growth
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	Moreover, our innovative sales and marketing programs combine active outreach and awareness campaigns with patient
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209;centric marketing programs in order to most effectively reach our target populations. We endeavor to continue to develop multiple sites because we believe regional density creates value through leverage in managed care contracting and greater brand awareness.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	Distinctive Real Estate Development Strategy Supports Attractive Unit Growth and Economics
</FONT>

<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">

	We have built an internal team with significant experience in multi
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209;unit retail expansion strategy and execution. As a result, our approach to real estate planning is highly consumer
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209;centric with a discipline traditionally utilized by sophisticated retail businesses. Our proprietary site selection model is a key to the success of our business, allowing us to identify and fill critical voids in community healthcare delivery systems. When combined with our scalable operating structure and attractive new facility model, our real estate development strategy allows us to maximize performance and quickly grow our facility base. Our seasoned real estate planning and development team follows a proven and disciplined strategy that leverages advanced data analytics to identify opportunities to provide underserved communities with high
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209;quality emergency care.
</FONT>

	This development model has also proven commercially successful in highly competitive markets and is currently supporting growth outside of our home state of Texas. Our sophisticated selection guidelines and scalable procedures allow us to open a new facility within 14 to 21&nbsp;months of site selection, enabling us to quickly capitalize on emerging opportunities. We have experienced rapid growth in recent periods, growing from 14 freestanding facilities at

<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">

Consequently, our facilities offer a positive work environment that leads to high retention rates and strong customer and provider relationships. We believe these programs will allow us to continue to effectively recruit physicians and clinicians to support our robust pipeline of new facilities.

<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 10PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">

<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209;quality care delivery, strong unit economics, disciplined development strategy and significant management experience. We plan to pursue the following growth strategies:

<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 10PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">

	We believe there is a significant opportunity to expand in our existing markets including Dallas/Fort Worth, Houston, San Antonio and Austin, Texas; Colorado Springs and Denver, Colorado; and Phoenix, Arizona. Our scale, scope and leading market position, combined with our sophisticated, proven site selection and development processes provide us with competitive advantages to continue to expand our facility base in these markets. We endeavor to continue to develop multiple sites because we believe regional density creates value through leverage in managed care contracting and greater brand awareness. We anticipate that as we further build our brand and increase the visibility of our facilities in our existing markets these efforts will increase patient awareness, and drive patient volume and same
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209;store growth.

<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 10PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	Build Strategic Alliances with Leading Health Systems
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 10PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	Development of our existing and new health system alliances is an important part of our continued growth. We expect to be a key partner for health systems seeking to enhance their local community presence through direct admissions relationships and new innovative partnerships. Our alliance with HCA in North Texas provides an example of one such innovative partnership, giving our patients direct access to HCA&#x2019;s approximately
</FONT>

	7,000 physicians and 15 hospitals in North Texas and Oklahoma and approximately 3,300 physicians and 9&nbsp;hospitals in the Houston area
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	. In addition, we have a relationship with the Concentra urgent care clinics in the Dallas/Fort Worth market, whereby we are

<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 10PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	Pursue a Disciplined Development Strategy in New States and Markets
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 10PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	We intend to continue expanding our facility base through new facility openings in new states and markets by leveraging our core capabilities in site selection, development and efficient facility openings. We view expansion as a core competency and see a significant opportunity to replicate the regional platform model established in Texas in new geographic markets. We entered the Colorado market in 2013, where we now have
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	15
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	freestanding facilities as part of our partnership with UCHealth, and the Arizona market in 2015, through our partnership with Dignity Health, with four freestanding facilities and a full
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209;service general hospital in the Phoenix area that has 16 inpatient rooms, two operating rooms, a nine
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209;room emergency department, a high
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209;complexity laboratory and a full radiology suite and we now have five freestanding facilities.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	In addition, we have recently announced joint venture partnerships with Ochsner Health in Louisiana and Mount Carmel Health System in Ohio.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	We have experienced rapid growth in recent periods, growing from 14 freestanding facilities at the end of 2012 to 81 freestanding facilities and two fully licensed general hospitals as of December 31,&nbsp;2015. We have a robust pipeline under development designed to support the addition of approximately 24 facilities in 2016. As we expand into new markets, particularly in states with complex regulatory requirements, we believe there is a potential to implement different operating models, such as innovative hospital partnership models, including a hospital hub and freestanding emergency room satellite model.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	Operations
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	Our operations consist primarily of our ownership and/or management of freestanding emergency care facilities, in addition to two full service licensed general hospitals. We provide patients prompt access to high
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209;quality, Board
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209;certified physicians and emergency trained registered nurses capable of handling all emergency issues and a wide array of treatments on
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209;site. We believe our acuity mix is comparable to hospital
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209;based emergency rooms. Our facilities provide the space and equipment necessary to enable our staff to provide quality emergency care. Each of our facilities is equipped with a full radiology suite, including CT scanners, digital x
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209;ray and ultrasound, as well as on
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209;site laboratories certified by CLIA and accredited by COLA. Every facility has transfer agreements in place with local hospitals for patients that need to be transferred to a hospital. In North Texas and the Houston area, we have entered into alliances with HCA to enhance the continuum of care for our patients by streamlining clinical protocols for transfers to hospitals and providing direct access to approximately
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	7,000 physicians and 15 hospitals in North Texas and Oklahoma and appro
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	ximately 3,300 physicians and 9
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&nbsp;hospitals in the Houston area,
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	for follow
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209;up care. We have similar clinical protocols with Dignity Health in Arizona and UCHealth in Colorado.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	Facilities
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	As of December 31, 2015, we had 83 facilities including two full service licensed general hospitals. We have 63 facilities in Texas, 15 facilities in Colorado in partnership with UCHealth and five facilities in Arizona in partnership Dignity Health. Our facilities are open 24&nbsp;hours a day, seven days a week, and are designed to ensure that our patients receive high
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209;quality, rapid, comfortable and convenient emergency medical care. Each
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	of our freestanding
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	facilit
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	ies
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	typically has six to nine emergency exam rooms. These include two high
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209;acuity suites, one &#x201C;child
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209;friendly&#x201D; pediatric room intended to create a comfortable environment for children, and a specialized obstetrics/gynecology room. All of our
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	freestanding
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	facilities have a centralized nurses&#x2019; station that acts as the command center providing easy access to our laboratory, radiology suite, supply rooms and secured narcotics area, in addition to being placed so that it maximizes the staff&#x2019;s line of sight to our suites and exam rooms. If a patient needs to be transported to a hospital, our
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	freestanding
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	facilities have ambulance bays that that are located near the emergency suites, providing for rapid and efficient access for emergency medical services personnel.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
</FONT>
</P>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="MARGIN-LEFT:10.2941176470588%;MARGIN-RIGHT:10.2941176470588%;">
<P>
<FONT SIZE="1">
</FONT>
</P>
<DIV STYLE="WIDTH:100%">
<P STYLE="MARGIN:24PT 0PT 0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:CENTER;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	12
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
</FONT>
</P>
</DIV>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="MARGIN-LEFT:10.2941176470588%;MARGIN-RIGHT:10.2941176470588%;">
<HR ALIGN="CENTER" STYLE='BACKGROUND-COLOR:#000000; BORDER-WIDTH:0; COLOR:#000000; HEIGHT:2PT; LINEHEIGHT:0; WIDTH:100%;'>

<P STYLE="PAGE-BREAK-AFTER:ALWAYS">
	&nbsp;
</P>
<A NAME="eolPage13"></A>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="MARGIN-LEFT:10.2941176470588%;MARGIN-RIGHT:10.2941176470588%;">
<DIV STYLE="WIDTH:100%">
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 6PT;COLOR:#0563C1;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<A HREF="#ADPT-20151231X10K_HTM_TOC">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#0563C1;">
	Table of Contents
</FONT>
</A>
</P>
</DIV>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="MARGIN-LEFT:10.2941176470588%;MARGIN-RIGHT:10.2941176470588%;">
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	Each of our emergency rooms contains a laboratory that is certified by CLIA and accredited by COLA. CLIA defines our laboratories as &#x201C;moderate complexity labs,&#x201D; which can perform &#x201C;waived&#x201D; and automated tests. The CLIA
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209;waived tests that we most commonly perform include, but not are limited to, rapid strep, influenza, and respiratory syncytial virus and blood glucose levels. Additionally, there are moderate complexity automated tests that include chemistries, cardiac enzymes, complete blood counts, clotting studies, and a variety of other pertinent diagnostic assessments. All in
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209;house testing provides results within approximately 20 minutes and those results are immediately provided to the physician for a more efficient diagnostic process. Additional testing which would require pathologist review, such as cultures and sub
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209;specialty samples, are managed through our relationships with accredited third
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209;party laboratories. Each laboratory department is supervised by a facility medical director, who acts as the dedicated laboratory director, overseeing all policies, testing, and ongoing operations.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	Our facilities are equipped with full radiology suites, including CT scanners, digital x
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209;rays and ultrasounds. Staffed around the clock with a licensed radiology technologist, our radiology suites are a critical component to the high
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209;quality care that we provide. Each radiology technologist has a minimum of two years of experience on both the CT and x
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209;ray modalities in a hospital setting. Our ultrasound machines are operated by certified on
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209;call ultrasound technologists that provide around
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209;the
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209;clock coverage for all of our facilities. All imaging studies are then interpreted off
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209;site by a contracted group of Board
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209;certified radiologists that are required to provide final reads within 30 minutes, 24&nbsp;hours a day, seven days a week.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	In addition to our carefully planned layout, laboratories and radiology suites, our facilities are also generally equipped with other features comparable to hospital emergency rooms. Our facilities are equipped with life
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209;safety code air systems with specialized ventilation and central oxygen with back
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209;up generators to ensure uninterrupted operations.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	The below image depicts t
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	he typical layout of one of our freestanding
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	facilities which range in size from approximately 6,000 to 7,000 square feet:
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;TEXT-ALIGN:CENTER;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
<IMG SRC="http://content.edgar-online.com/edgar_conv_img/2016/02/29/0001558370-16-003672_ADPT20151231X10K002.JPG" STYLE="WIDTH: 6.239583IN; HEIGHT: 3.333333IN" ALT="PICTURE 5">
</FONT>

<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;TEXT-ALIGN:CENTER;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	Staffing
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	We employ a base &#x201C;1
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209;1
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209;1
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209;1&#x201D; model for our staffing needs at each freestanding facility, meaning that we have a minimum of one Board
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209;certified physician, one emergency trained registered nurse, one radiology technologist and one
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
</FONT>
</P>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="MARGIN-LEFT:10.2941176470588%;MARGIN-RIGHT:10.2941176470588%;">

<DIV STYLE="WIDTH:100%">

	Table of Contents

<DIV STYLE="MARGIN-LEFT:10.2941176470588%;MARGIN-RIGHT:10.2941176470588%;">
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	front office staff member on
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209;site at all times. This is a fixed cost labor model as all facilities are open 24&nbsp;hours a day, seven days a week. This base staffing can be augmented during periods of high
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209;patient volume. We operate using two 12
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209;hour shifts per day, beginning at 7:00&nbsp;a.m. and 7:00&nbsp;p.m. Each facility utilizes approximately 35 staff members, made up of four full
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209;time and five part
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209;time employees per function. Our full
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209;time employees work three 12
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209;hour shifts per week. Each of our facilities also has a facility administrator, who is also the nurse manager. The facility administrator is in charge of all operating aspects of the facility and the coordination of care to patients.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	Our physicians are contracted through
</FONT>
<A NAME="ADPT-20151231X10K_HTM__CP_TEXT_1_103">
</A>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	National Medical Professionals of Texas
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	PLLC,
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	National Medical Professionals of Colorado
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	PLLC and National Medical Professionals of Arizona LLC,
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	affiliated professional limited liability compan
</FONT>
<A NAME="ADPT-20151231X10K_HTM__CP_TEXT_1_105">
</A>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	ies
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	owned by our Executive Medical Director that handles our physician
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209;staffing needs in each of the markets where we operate. We currently utilize
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	over
</FONT>
<A NAME="ADPT-20151231X10K_HTM__CP_TEXT_1_107">
</A>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	606
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	accredited Board
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209;certified physicians.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	We provide physicians with a unique and attractive opportunity to practice emergency medicine in a work environment with a reduced administrative workload, scheduling flexibility and a covered cost of malpractice insurance, which allows our physicians to focus on providing high
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209;quality care. Our model allows physicians to spend more time with each patient and thus the ability to focus their attention on the patient in order to deliver quality care.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	Our physician recruiters identify and source talent through a variety of methods, including networking, targeted job postings and employee referrals. Once a candidate has been identified, we invite them on
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209;site to tour our facility and meet with the facility medical director. If the candidate is a fit, a rigorous credentialing process is initiated that verifies the candidate&#x2019;s education, training, state licensing, experience, current health status and clinical competence.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	All of our physicians sign a physician services agreement, which sets forth their duties and responsibilities, assigns each physician to a home facility, outlines shift commitments and guarantees and contains a 90
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209;day notice of termination provision for both parties. Each facility has a facility medical director, who is the physician responsible for providing clinical guidance and oversight, performing chart reviews, ensuring compliance with infection control protocols and acting as the laboratory director for the facility.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	Patients
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	Our
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	e
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	mergency
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	r
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	ooms provide access to high
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209;quality emergency care in the neighborhoods near each site. Typically
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	, &nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	approximately 60% of each facility&#x2019;s patients come from a three
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209;mile radius, with approximately 80% coming from a five
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209;mile radius. Our
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	fa
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	cilities treat a wide array of emergency patient problems, such as heart attacks, severe abdominal pain and respiratory distress.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	Patient satisfaction for
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	our e
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	mergency
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	r
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	oom care is among the highest in the nation. First Choice Emergency Room was named a Guardian of Excellence Award winner in 2013, 2014 and 2015 by Press Ganey. This award recognizes top
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209;performing facilities from among participating member hospital emergency rooms that are in the 95
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:5PT;TOP:-4PT;POSITION:RELATIVE;LINE-HEIGHT:100%">
	th
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&nbsp;percentile of performance in patient satisfaction nationwide, and is a healthcare industry symbol of achievement.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	Illustrative Patient Experiences at First Choice Emergency Rooms
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	We believe we are transforming the emergency care experience with a differentiated care delivery model, as demonstrated by the below sampling of experiences our patients have had at First Choice Emergency Rooms:
</FONT>
</P>
<DIV STYLE="WIDTH:100%">
<TABLE STYLE="WIDTH:100%;" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0">
<TR>
<TD STYLE="WIDTH:36PT;">
<P STYLE="WIDTH:36PT;FONT-SIZE:0PT;">
</P>
</TD>
<TD VALIGN="TOP" ALIGN="LEFT" STYLE="WIDTH: 17.00PT; DISPLAY: INLINE;">
<P STYLE="BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;">
<FONT STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;FONT-FAMILY:SYMBOL;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-SIZE:10PT;;">
	&#xB7;
</FONT>
</P>
</TD>
<TD STYLE="WIDTH:1PT;">
<P STYLE="WIDTH:1PT;WIDTH:1PT;FONT-SIZE:0PT;">
</P>
</TD>
<TD ALIGN="LEFT" VALIGN="TOP">
<P STYLE="BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;COLOR:#000000;">
	Cardiac Event.&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	A man came to the nearby First Choice Emergency Room after experiencing chest pain and shortness of breath for over a day. Within minutes of his arrival he was given an electrocardiogram, which indicated a possible heart attack. While getting his chest x
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	&#8209;ray, his heart stopped beating. The clinical team administered CPR and the patient had a near immediate return of spontaneous circulation. The CT scan showed a large &#x201C;saddle emboli&#x201D; (a large blood clot straddling the blood vessels) in his heart and more in his pulmonary vasculature (blood vessels of the lungs). He was anti
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	&#8209;coagulated and transferred to the hospital catheterization laboratory.
</FONT>
</P>
</TD>
</TR>
</TABLE>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="WIDTH:100%">
<TABLE STYLE="WIDTH:100%;" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0">
<TR>
<TD STYLE="WIDTH:36PT;">
<P STYLE="WIDTH:36PT;FONT-SIZE:0PT;">
</P>
</TD>
<TD VALIGN="TOP" ALIGN="LEFT" STYLE="WIDTH: 17.00PT; DISPLAY: INLINE;">
<P STYLE="BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;">
<FONT STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;FONT-FAMILY:SYMBOL;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-SIZE:10PT;;">
	&#xB7;
</FONT>
</P>
</TD>
<TD STYLE="WIDTH:1PT;">
<P STYLE="WIDTH:1PT;WIDTH:1PT;FONT-SIZE:0PT;">
</P>
</TD>
<TD ALIGN="LEFT" VALIGN="TOP">
<P STYLE="BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;COLOR:#000000;">
	Premature Delivery Complication.&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	A 34
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	&#8209;week pregnant woman was rushed into a First Choice Emergency Room in active labor. The baby had already begun to crown and both mother and baby
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
</FONT>
</P>
</TD>

<DIV STYLE="MARGIN-LEFT:10.2941176470588%;MARGIN-RIGHT:10.2941176470588%;">
<DIV STYLE="WIDTH:100%">
<TABLE STYLE="WIDTH:100%;" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0">
<TR>
<TD ALIGN="LEFT" VALIGN="TOP">
<P STYLE="BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	appeared to be in distress. Within four minutes of the patient&#x2019;s arrival, the baby was delivered. The delivery was complicated by the umbilical cord being wrapped around the baby&#x2019;s neck, a life
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	&#8209;threatening complication. Our physician properly handled the delivery and as a result both the mother and baby were healthy.
</FONT>
</P>
</TD>
</TR>
</TABLE>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="WIDTH:100%">
<TABLE STYLE="WIDTH:100%;" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0">
<TR>
<TD STYLE="WIDTH:36PT;">
<P STYLE="WIDTH:36PT;FONT-SIZE:0PT;">
</P>
</TD>
<TD VALIGN="TOP" ALIGN="LEFT" STYLE="WIDTH: 17.00PT; DISPLAY: INLINE;">
<P STYLE="BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;">
<FONT STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;FONT-FAMILY:SYMBOL;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-SIZE:10PT;;">
	&#xB7;
</FONT>
</P>
</TD>
<TD STYLE="WIDTH:1PT;">
<P STYLE="WIDTH:1PT;WIDTH:1PT;FONT-SIZE:0PT;">
</P>
</TD>
<TD ALIGN="LEFT" VALIGN="TOP">
<P STYLE="BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;COLOR:#000000;">
	Respiratory Distress.&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	A nearby family practice physician was experiencing shortness of breath and came into a First Choice Emergency Room. Within minutes, her shortness of breath became very severe. Our physician had to intubate (placing a breathing tube into the trachea to allow for mechanical ventilation) the patient to ensure adequate ventilation and oxygenation&#x2014;a life
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	&#8209;saving measure. The patient was then transported to a nearby hospital to see a thoracic specialist. She has now recovered and regularly refers her patients, as well as her family, to First Choice Emergency Rooms for emergency care.
</FONT>
</P>
</TD>
</TR>
</TABLE>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="WIDTH:100%">
<TABLE STYLE="WIDTH:100%;" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0">
<TR>
<TD STYLE="WIDTH:36PT;">
<P STYLE="WIDTH:36PT;FONT-SIZE:0PT;">
</P>
</TD>
<TD VALIGN="TOP" ALIGN="LEFT" STYLE="WIDTH: 17.00PT; DISPLAY: INLINE;">
<P STYLE="BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;">
<FONT STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;FONT-FAMILY:SYMBOL;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-SIZE:10PT;;">
	&#xB7;
</FONT>
</P>
</TD>
<TD STYLE="WIDTH:1PT;">
<P STYLE="WIDTH:1PT;WIDTH:1PT;FONT-SIZE:0PT;">
</P>
</TD>
<TD ALIGN="LEFT" VALIGN="TOP">
<P STYLE="BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;COLOR:#000000;">
	Accidental Poisoning.&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	A one
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	&#8209;year
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	&#8209;old girl was brought to a First Choice Emergency Room after accidentally drinking toxic cleaning solution. During the three
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	&#8209;minute drive, the young girl elevated from having no symptoms to an almost complete inability to breathe. The First Choice Emergency Room staff immediately treated the patient and the child fully recovered
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	.
</FONT>
</P>
</TD>
</TR>
</TABLE>
</DIV>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	Licensing and Accreditation
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	All of our facilities are licensed pursuant to state
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209;specific licensing requirements.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	Our hospital facility in Texas is licensed as a &#x201C;General Hospital&#x201D; under the administration of the Texas Department of State Health Services (
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#x201C;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	TDSHS
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#x201D;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	) on a bi-annual basis. All of the freestanding facilities in Dallas/Fort Worth are outpatient departments of the Texas Hospital (
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#x201C;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	HOPD&#x2019;s
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#x201D;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	)
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	The other
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	Texas
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	freestanding
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	facilities are licensed as &#x201C;Freestanding Emergen
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	cy Medical Care Facilities&#x201D; by the TDSHS
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	on a bi
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209;annual basi
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	s. Our facilities in Colorado are licensed as &#x201C;Community Clinics with Emergency Centers&#x201D; under the administration of the Colorado Department of Public Health and Environment, Health Facilities and Emergency Medical Services Division on an annual basis. Our hospital facility in Arizona in partnership with Dignity Health is licensed as a &#x201C;General Hospital&#x201D; under the administration of the Arizon
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	a Department of Health Services (
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#x201C;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	AZDHS
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#x201D;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	) on an annual basis. The HOPD&#x2019;s in Arizona are licensed as Outpatient Treatment Centers as satellites of the hospital and renew with
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	the hospital license.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	All non-HOPD facilities in Texas and all Colorado facilities
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	are accredited as an Ambulatory System
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	and both hospitals in Texas and Arizona are accredited as Hospitals by the Joint Commission
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	. An independent, not
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209;for
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209;profit organization, the Joint Commission is the nation&#x2019;s oldest and largest standards
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209;setting and accrediting body in healthcare. Since 1975, the Joint Commission has developed state
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209;of
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209;the
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209;art standards for outpatient ambulatory care organizations. By demonstrating compliance with the Joint Commission&#x2019;s national standards for healthcare quality and safety,
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	all freestanding facilities have
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	earned the Joint Commission&#x2019;s Gold Seal of Approval. The accreditation award recognizes
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	our
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	dedication to continuously comply with the Joint Commission&#x2019;s state
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209;of
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209;the
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209;art standards.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	Risk Management
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	We have various committees comprised of physicians and clinical personnel that discuss and set internal policies regarding various risk management issues including safety and environment of care, infection control, pharmacy and therapeutics, quality assessment and performance improvement, peer review and chart review. The policies we establish comply with relevant state, federal and regulatory and Joint Commission requirements.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	Billing and Payment
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	We obtain patient service revenues by collecting fees from patients, insurance companies, and other third
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209;party payors for the professional and technical services provided in our facilities.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	Prior
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	to October 1, 2015, billing and coding was done by a centralized team. On October 1, 2015, all billing and coding was outsourced to a
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	third
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	-
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	party to ensure compliance with ICD-10 coding requirements. Our general practice, where possible, is to collect estimated co
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209;payments at the facility.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
</FONT>
</P>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="MARGIN-LEFT:10.2941176470588%;MARGIN-RIGHT:10.2941176470588%;">
<P>
<FONT SIZE="1">
</FONT>
</P>
<DIV STYLE="WIDTH:100%">
<P STYLE="MARGIN:24PT 0PT 0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:CENTER;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	15
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
</FONT>
</P>
</DIV>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="MARGIN-LEFT:10.2941176470588%;MARGIN-RIGHT:10.2941176470588%;">
