<P STYLE="MARGIN:5PT 0PT 5PT 10PT;BACKGROUND-COLOR: #FFFFFF;TEXT-INDENT: -10PT;COLOR:#000000;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;COLOR:#000000;">
	Internal Control over Financial Reporting
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:13.2PT 0PT 12PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;COLOR:#000000;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	As of December&nbsp;31, 2015, we had one material weakness in our internal control over financial reporting. A material weakness is a deficiency, or a combination of control deficiencies, in internal control over financial reporting, such that there is a reasonable possibility that a material misstatement of the annual or interim consolidated financial statements will not be prevented or detected on a timely basis.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	The Company&#x2019;s risk assessment process failed to design and implement appropriate process level and monitoring controls over revenue billing transactions and related accounts receivable performed by a third-party service provider on our behalf as of December 31, 2015.&nbsp;&nbsp;Additionally, the Company&#x2019;s internal control activities designed to ensure revenue transaction data being transferred to the third-party service provider is complete and accurate were not operating effectively as of December 31, 2015.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;BACKGROUND-COLOR: #FFFFFF;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;COLOR:#000000;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	To remediate the material weakness, the Company intends to receive an adequate verification of the suitability of the design and operating effectiveness of controls relating to the system and business processing activities performed by the service organization for the year ended December 31, 2016.&nbsp;&nbsp;Additionally, the Company will implement controls prior to data being transferred to the third-party service provider to ensure completeness and accuracy over patient encounter documentation.&nbsp;&nbsp;See &#x201C;Risk Factors&#x2014;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	Risks Related to Our Organizational Structure
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	&#x2014;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	We have identified a material weakness in our internal control over financial reporting that, if not corrected, could result in material misstatements of our financial statements.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	&#x201D; and &#x201C;Risk Factors&#x2014;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	Risks Related to Our Organizational Structure
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	&#x2014;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	If we are unable to maintain effective internal control over financial reporting, our ability to report our financial results on a timely and accurate basis may be adversely affected, which in turn could cause the market price of our common stock to decline.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	&#x201D;
</FONT>
</P>
<EFX_RESULTS_OF_OPERATIONS>
<A NAME="FIS_RESULTS_OF_OPERATIONS"></A>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:12PT 0PT 10PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	Components of Results of Operations
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 10PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	Revenue
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 10PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	Patient Service Revenue
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 10PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	Patient service revenue primarily consists of charges for the professional and technical services provided to patients, net of contractual allowance, charity care write
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209;offs, and self
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209;pay discounts. Revenue is recognized when services are rendered to patients. Charges for all services provided to insured patients are initially billed to and processed by the patients&#x2019; insurance provider. Allowed amounts not covered by the insurance companies are then billed to the patients. Collection of payment for services provided to patients without insurance coverage is done at the time of service.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 10PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
</FONT>
</P>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="MARGIN-LEFT:10.2941176470588%;MARGIN-RIGHT:10.2941176470588%;">
<P>
<FONT SIZE="1">
</FONT>
</P>
<DIV STYLE="WIDTH:100%">
<P STYLE="MARGIN:24PT 0PT 0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:CENTER;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	62
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
</FONT>
</P>
</DIV>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="MARGIN-LEFT:10.2941176470588%;MARGIN-RIGHT:10.2941176470588%;">

<P STYLE="PAGE-BREAK-AFTER:ALWAYS">
	&nbsp;
</P>
<A NAME="eolPage63"></A>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="MARGIN-LEFT:10.2941176470588%;MARGIN-RIGHT:10.2941176470588%;">
<DIV STYLE="WIDTH:100%">
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 6PT;COLOR:#0563C1;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<A HREF="#ADPT-20151231X10K_HTM_TOC">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#0563C1;">
	Table of Contents
</FONT>
</A>
</P>
</DIV>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="MARGIN-LEFT:10.2941176470588%;MARGIN-RIGHT:10.2941176470588%;">
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 10PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	Provision for Bad Debt
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 10PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	Provision for bad debt primarily consists of the estimated uncollectible amounts from insured patients. Provision for bad debt is taken in the quarter the services are provided.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 10PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	Management and Contract Services Revenue
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 10PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	Management and contract services revenue consists of income we earn in exchange for managing the day-to-day operations of our joint venture; and is calculated as a percentage of the joint venture&#x2019;s net revenues
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 10PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	Equity in Earnings (Loss) of Unconsolidated Joint Ventures
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 10PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	Equity in the earnings (loss) of unconsolidated joint ventures consists of our share of the net income (loss) of our joint ventures, which is based on the joint venture&#x2019;s net loss and the percentage of the joint venture&#x2019;s outstanding equity interests owned by us. We receive and annual preferred return up to a specified amount on our investment in the joint venture prior to proportionate distributions to the partners.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	This preferred return resets annually in April of each year and can result in a disproportionate amount of earnings of the joint venture being recognized by the Company in the early part of the fiscal year.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 10PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	Operating Expenses
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 10PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	Salaries, Wages and Benefits
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	Salaries, wages and benefits primarily consist of contract payments to our physicians and compensation and benefits to our staff at our facilities and corporate office, including non
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209;cash stock compensation related to restricted shares with time
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209; or performance
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209;based vesting schedules. Salaries, wages and benefits also includes certain labor costs associated with the opening of new facilities. We typically incur higher than normal employee costs at the time of a facility opening associated with set
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209;up and other opening costs. We employ a base &#x201C;1
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209;1
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209;1
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209;1&#x201D; model for our staffing needs at each freestanding facility, meaning that we have a minimum of one Board
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209;certified physician, one emergency trained registered nurse, one radiology technologist and one front office staff member on
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209;site at all times. This is a fixed cost labor model as all facilities are open 24&nbsp;hours a day, seven days a week.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	General and Administrative
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	General and administrative expenses primarily consist of marketing, utilities, medical malpractice and other insurance, professional fees, training and development, travel, office and computer, certain preopening costs incurred in connection with the opening of a facility and Advisory Services Agreement fees and expenses. Our marketing activities are principally focused on building awareness in the community to drive patient volume. We utilize targeted marketing efforts within local neighborhoods, through channels such as direct mail, mobile billboards, radio advertisements, television, community sponsorships and a robust online/social media presence.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	Other Operating Expenses
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	Other operating expenses primarily consist of facility and equipment lease costs, medical and laboratory supplies, radiology fees and facility maintenance. We lease the majority of our facilities under operating leases with terms ranging from five to 15&nbsp;years. These leases typically have renewal options. We also lease certain medical equipment under various non
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209;cancelable operating leases. With the exception of medical and laboratory supplies and radiology fees the facility expenses are fixed in nature.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	Depreciation and Amortization
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	Depreciation and amortization is related to buildings, equipment and leasehold improvements whose cost is depreciated or amortized over the shorter of the non
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209;cancellable lease term or the estimated useful life of the asset.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
</FONT>
</P>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="MARGIN-LEFT:10.2941176470588%;MARGIN-RIGHT:10.2941176470588%;">

<FONT SIZE="1">
</FONT>
</P>
<DIV STYLE="WIDTH:100%">

<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	Other Income (Expense)
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	Gain on Contribution to Joint Venture
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="TEXT-INDENT:0PT;MARGIN-LEFT:0PT; PADDING-RIGHT:4PT;">
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="TEXT-INDENT:0PT;MARGIN-LEFT:0PT; PADDING-RIGHT:4PT;TEXT-ALIGN:LEFT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	Gain on contribution to joint venture c
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	onsists of
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	a gain recognized on the contribution and change of control of previously owned freestanding facilities to the joint venture with UCHealth.
</FONT>
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	Interest Expense
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	Interest expense primarily consists of interest on our Senior Secured Credit Facility and on one facility treated as a capital lease.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	Realized Loss on Derivative
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	Realized loss on derivative consists of the loss reclassified into earnings in the current period on the changes in fair value of an interest rate contract
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	Loss on Extinguishment of Debt
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	Loss on extin
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	g
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	uishment of debt consists of loss related to the write-off of loan origination costs associated with the credit facility that was repaid in in 2015 and the prepayment penalty incurred on the early payoff.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	Provision (Benefit) for Income Taxes
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	As of December 31, 2015, we
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	had a net operating loss carryforward of approximately $4.2 million. If not utilized, our federal operating loss carryforward will expire in 2034. A cumulative change in ownership
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	among material shareholders, as defined in Section 382 of the Internal Revenue Code, during a three-year period may limit utilization of the federal net operating loss carryforwards.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">

<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	Overall
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	Our results for the year ended December 31, 2015 reflect a 66.4% increase in net patient service revenue of $139.8&nbsp;million. We recorded net income of $32.8&nbsp;million compared to a net loss of $17.3&nbsp;million for the year ended December 31, 2014. The increase in net income was attributable to an increase of $154.0 million in net operating revenue, a $14.2 million increase in management and contract services revenue and a $9.8 million increase in equity in earnings of unconsolidated joint ventures,
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	coupled with a $24.3 million gain
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	recognized on the contribution
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	of existing freestanding facilities to the joint venture with University of Colorado Health.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	This increase was partially offset by
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	increases in salaries, wages and benefits and other costs related to our growth initiatives
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	,
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	a $5.0 million loss on extinguishment of debt,
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	an
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	increase in depreciation and amortization expense
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	and the impact of taxes on higher earnings
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	Revenue
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT 36PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	Patient Service Revenue
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	Patient service revenue increased by $177.3&nbsp;million, or 72.9%, to $420.6&nbsp;million for the year ended December 31, 2015, from $243.3&nbsp;million for the year ended December 31, 2014. This increase was primarily attributable to the impact of patient volumes from the expansion of the number of consolidated freestanding facilities from 46 to 62 and annual gross charge increases, offset by the deconsolidation of our Colorado locations due to the UCHealth joint venture.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT 36PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">

</FONT>

<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT 36PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	Provision for Bad Debt
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	Our provision for bad debt increased by $37.5&nbsp;million to $70.1&nbsp;million for the year ended December 31, 2015, from $32.6&nbsp;million for the year ended December 31, 2014. This increase was primarily attributable to
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	a shift in payor mix from third-party payors to patients, coupled with
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	bad debt associated with revenue generated from the expansion of the number of consolidated freestanding facilities from 46 to 62.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT 36PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	Net Patient Service Revenue
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	As a result of the factors described above, our net patient service revenue increased by $139.8 million, or 66.4%, to $350.5&nbsp;million for the year ended December 31, 2015, from $210.7&nbsp;million for the year ended December 31, 2014.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	Management and Contract Services Revenue
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	Management and contract services revenue was approximately $14.2 million for the year ended December 31, 2015 compared to approximately $20,000 for the year ended December 31, 2014.&nbsp;&nbsp;The increase is a result of our management and contract services agreement associated with our joint venture agreement entered into in November 2014 and April 2015
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	Equity in earnings (loss) of joint ventures
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 10PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	Equity in earnings (loss) of joint ventures consists of our 49.9% share of earnings (losses) generated from our non-controlling equity investments. Our equity in earnings (losses) of unconsolidated joint ventures increased by $9.8 million to $8.9 million for the year ended December 31, 2015 from a loss of approximately $0.9 million for the year ended December 31, 2014.&nbsp;&nbsp;The increase is primarily attributable to earnings generated from our non-controlling equity investment in Colorado, in which t
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	he Company receives an annual preferred return up to a specified amount on its investment in the joint venture prior to proportionate distributions to the partners.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	Operating Expenses
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT 36PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	Salaries, Wages and Benefits
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	Salaries, wages and benefits increased by $81.6&nbsp;million to $218.1&nbsp;million for the year ended December 31, 2015, from $136.5&nbsp;million for the year ended December 31, 2014. This increase was primarily attributable to our continued efforts to support new facility growth, including $47.7 million for physician labor, which includes both owned and managed facil
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	i
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	ties as we provide physician services to each facility, $21.9 million related to staffing at facilities, $10.1 million related to Corporate staffing and $1.8 million in stock compensation expense.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT 36PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">

<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	General and administrative expenses increased by $13.5&nbsp;million to $51.1&nbsp;million for the year ended December 31, 2015, from $37.6&nbsp;million for the year ended December 31, 2014. This increase was primarily attributable to $1.7 million in additional marketing costs associated with opening new facilities and our consumer awareness program, $2.6&nbsp;million in additional facility utilities and insurance expenses, $1.4 million in property taxes, $6.1&nbsp;million in legal and accounting expenses associated with opening new facilities and Sarbanes-Oxley readiness, $0.7&nbsp;million in travel expenses associated with increased headcount and the opening of new facilities outside of
</FONT>

	Other Operating Expenses
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	Other operating expenses increased by $24.1&nbsp;million to $51.4&nbsp;million for the year ended December 31, 2015, from $27.3&nbsp;million for the year ended December 31, 2014. This increase was primarily attributable to $14.7&nbsp;million in additional lease costs for buildings and medical equipment at facilities, $0.7 million increase in lease costs for corporate office space, $2.6&nbsp;million in property insurance and building maintenance for new and existing facilities, $0.2 million in outsourcing hospital cafeteria/services, $0.2 million in restructuring costs related to outsourcing billing and collections for ICD-10 co
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	mpliance
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	and $0.1 million related to the disposal of equipment in the normal course of business. Patient care and supply costs increased by $5.6 million across all facilities.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT 36PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	Depreciation and Amortization
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	Depreciation and amortization expenses increased by $2.8&nbsp;million to $17.9&nbsp;million for the year ended December 31, 2015, from $15.0&nbsp;million for the year ended December 31, 2014. This increase was primarily attributable to the construction of new facilities that opened during 2015 and 2014, as well as new equipment at those facilities.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">

</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;TEXT-INDENT:40.5PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	The Company recorded a gain of $24.3 million for the year ended December 31, 2015 as a result of the contribution and change of control of previously owned freestanding facilities to the joint venture with UCHealth.

<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	Loss on Extinguishment of Debt
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">

<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	Income (Loss) Before Provision (Benefit) for Income Taxes
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	As a result of the factors described above, we recorded a loss before (benefit) provision for income taxes of $41.6&nbsp;million for the year ended December 31, 2015, compared to a net loss of $18.6&nbsp;million for the year ended December 31, 2014.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	Provision (Benefit) for Income Taxes
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	For the year ended December 31, 2015, we recorded income tax expense of $8.7 million, which consists of $7.1 million of federal income tax expense and Texas margin tax of $1.6 million. Prior to the Reorganization, we were not a federal taxpayer. The Company&#x2019;s effective tax rate for the period subsequent to the Reorganization differs from the statutory rate due primarily to state taxes that are not based on pre-tax income/(loss) but on gross margin resulting in state tax expense even in periods of pretax losses.
</FONT>
</P>

<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	Overall
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	Our results for the year ended December 31, 2014 reflect a 104.8% increase in net patient service revenue of $107.8&nbsp;million. We recorded a net loss of $17.3&nbsp;million compared to a net loss of $3.0&nbsp;million for the year ended December 31, 2013. The net loss was attributable to preopening expenses associated with 29 new facility openings and 2 relocations, interest expense associated with our long-term debt, additional depreciation and amortization expense and costs associated with our initial public offering and other public company costs, partially offset by an increase in net patient service revenue resulting from our growth.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">

	Patient service revenue increased by $128.3&nbsp;million, or 111.6%, to $243.3&nbsp;million for the year ended December 31, 2014 from $115.0&nbsp;million for the year ended December 31, 2013. This increase was primarily attributable to a 20.9%

<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	increase in patient volumes generated from new facilities, a 2.4% increase in the number of high acuity patients and a 5.0% overall increase in rates for certain third-party payors beginning in May 2014.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT 36PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	Provision for Bad Debt
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	Our provision for bad debt increased by $20.5&nbsp;million to $32.6&nbsp;million for the year ended December 31, 2014, from $12.1&nbsp;million for the year ended December 31, 2013. Of this increase, $18.5&nbsp;million was attributable to bad debt associated with revenue generated from new facilities and the remainder was attributable to an increase in patient volume coupled with a shift in payor mix from third-party payors to patients.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT 36PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	Net Patient Service Revenue
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	As a result of the factors described above, our net patient service revenue increased by $107.8&nbsp;million, or 104.8%, to $210.7&nbsp;million for the year ended December 31, 2014, from $102.9&nbsp;million for the year ended December 31, 2013.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">

	Management and contract services revenue was approximately $20,000 for the year ended December 31, 2014 as a result of our management and contract services agreement associated with our joint venture agreement entered into in November 2014
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:12PT;">

<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 10PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	Equity in loss of joint venture consists of our 49.9% share of losses generated from our non-controlling equity investment in a hospital facility located in Phoenix, Arizona. Our equity in loss of unconsolidated joint venture was approximately $0.9 million for the year ended December 31, 2014.
</FONT>

	Operating Expenses

<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT 36PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	Salaries, Wages and Benefits
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	Salaries, wages and benefits increased by $71.3&nbsp;million to $136.5&nbsp;million for the year ended December 31, 2014, from $65.2&nbsp;million for the year ended December 31, 2013. This increase was primarily attributable to an increase in new facilities, which contributed $63.0&nbsp;million in facility compensation. The remaining $8.3&nbsp;million increase was primarily attributable to our continued efforts to add staff to support new facility growth.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT 36PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	General and Administrative
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	General and administrative expenses increased by $20.2&nbsp;million to $37.6&nbsp;million for the year ended December 31, 2014, from $17.4&nbsp;million for the year ended December 31, 2013. This increase was primarily attributable to $5.2 million in costs associated with our initial public offering, $3.4 million in additional marketing costs associated with opening new facilities and our consumer awareness program, $3.5&nbsp;million in additional facility utilities and insurance expenses, $1.2 million in property taxes, $1.8&nbsp;million in legal and accounting expenses associated with opening new facilities, $1.3&nbsp;million in travel expenses associated with increased headcount and the opening of new facilities outside of the Dallas/Fort Worth market and $3.8 million in employee recruiting, development and other corporate expenses.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT 36PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">

<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	Other operating expenses increased by $16.1&nbsp;million to $27.3&nbsp;million for the year ended December 31, 2014, from $11.2&nbsp;million for the year ended December 31, 2013. This increase was primarily attributable to $10.8&nbsp;million in additional lease costs for buildings and medical equipment at facilities, $0.7 million increase in lease costs for corporate office space and $1.6&nbsp;million in property insurance and building maintenance for new and existing facilities. 	Depreciation and Amortization
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	Depreciation and amortization expenses increased by $7.1&nbsp;million to $15.0&nbsp;million for the year ended December 31, 2014, from $7.9&nbsp;million for the year ended December 31, 2013. This increase was primarily attributable to the construction of new facilities that opened during 2014 and 2013, as well as new equipment at those facilities.

</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	Other (Expense) Income
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT 36PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	Interest Expense
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	Interest expense primarily consists of interest on our Senior Secured Credit Facility and on one facility treated as a capital lease. Our interest expense increased by $9.1&nbsp;million to $12.0&nbsp;million for the year ended December 31, 2014, compared to $2.8&nbsp;million for the year ended December 31, 2013. This increase was primarily attributable to refinancing our Senior Secured Credit Facility in 2013 at higher interest rates, coupled with an increase in borrowings to fund construction of new facilities.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	Loss Before (Benefit) Provision for Income Taxes
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	As a result of the factors described above, we recorded a loss before (benefit) provision for income taxes of $18.6&nbsp;million for the year ended December 31, 2014, compared to a net loss of $2.3&nbsp;million for the year ended December 31, 2013.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	(Benefit) Provision for Income Taxes
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	For the year ended December 31, 2014, we recorded income tax benefit of $1.3 million, which consists of $2.8 million of federal income tax benefit offset by Texas margin tax of $1.5 million. Prior to the Reorganization, we were not a federal taxpayer. The Company&#x2019;s effective tax rate for the period subsequent to the Reorganization differs from the statutory rate due primarily to state taxes that are not based on pre-tax income/(loss) but on gross margin resulting in state tax expense even in periods of pretax losses.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">

<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	As a result of the factors described above, we recorded a net loss of $17.3&nbsp;million for the year ended December 31, 2014, compared to a net loss of $3.0&nbsp;million for the year ended December 31, 2013.
</FONT>

<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	Liquidity and Capital Resources
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:5PT 0PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	We rely on cash flows from operations, the Senior Secured Credit Facility and the MPT Agreements (each as described below) as our primary sources of liquidity. In June 2014, we sold 4,900,000 shares of Class A common stock in an initial public offering, resulting in proceeds, net of transaction expenses, of $96.2 million.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	We used part of the net proceeds from the initial public offering to reduce outstanding borrowings under our senior secured credit facility.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	An additional 735,000 shares of Class A common stock were sold to the public
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	, of which 313,586 shares were sold by a significant stockholder and 421,414 shares were sold by the Company with the proceeds received by the Company used to purchase an equivalent number of LLC Units from such significant stockholder
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:2.6PT 0PT 0PT 2PT;PUNCTUATION-WRAP:HANGING;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	&nbsp;

<P STYLE="MARGIN:2.9PT 5.75PT 12PT 0PT;PUNCTUATION-WRAP:HANGING;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	Upon the consummation of our initial public offering, we entered into a tax receivable agreement with the Unit holders of Adeptus Health LLC, which provides for the payment from time to time by us to the Unit holders of Adeptus Health LLC of 85% of the amount of the benefits, if any, that we deemed to realize as a result of increases in
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
</FONT>

<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 6PT;COLOR:#0563C1;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<A HREF="#ADPT-20151231X10K_HTM_TOC">

<DIV STYLE="MARGIN-LEFT:10.2941176470588%;MARGIN-RIGHT:10.2941176470588%;">
<P STYLE="MARGIN:2.9PT 5.75PT 12PT 0PT;PUNCTUATION-WRAP:HANGING;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	tax basis and certain other tax benefits related to exchanges of LLC Units pursuant to the exchange agreement, including tax benefits attributable to payments under the tax receivable agreement.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	These payment obligations are obligations of Adeptus Health Inc.; however, payments to LLC Unit holders will only be paid as tax benefits for the Company are realized.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	For purposes of the tax receivable agreement, the benefit deemed realized by Adeptus Health Inc. will be computed by comparing its actual income tax liability (calculated with certain assumptions) to the amount of such taxes that we would have been required to pay had there been no increase to the tax basis of the assets of Adeptus Health LLC as a result of the exchanges and had Adeptus Health Inc. not entered into the tax receivable agreement.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:2.6PT 0PT 0PT 2PT;PUNCTUATION-WRAP:HANGING;TEXT-INDENT:34PT;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	Our primary cash needs are capital expenditures on new facilities, compensation of our personnel, purchases of medical supplies, facility leases, equipment rentals, marketing initiatives, service of long-term debt and any payments made under the tax receivable agreement. We believe that cash we expect to generate from operations, the availability of borrowings under the Senior Secured Credit Facility and funds available under the MPT Agreements will be sufficient to meet liquidity requirements, including any payments made under the tax receivable agreement, anticipated capital expenditures and payments due under our Senior Secured Credit Facility and MPT Agreements for at least 12&nbsp;months.
</FONT>
</P>

<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	As of December 31, 2015, our principal sources of liquidity included cash of $16.0&nbsp;million, funds available under our Senior Secured Credit Facility line of credit of $50.0&nbsp;million, net of $10.2 million for outstanding letters of credit, subject to meeting certain debt covenants. 	had $201.7&nbsp;million available under the MPT Agreements.

<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT 36PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	Net Cash from Operating Activities
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	Net cash provided by operating activities increased by $37.8&nbsp;million to $13.1&nbsp;million for the year ended December 31,
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	2015, from $24.7&nbsp;million used&nbsp;&nbsp;by operating activities for the same period in 2014. This increase is primarily the result of the increase in net income of $50.1 million and an increase in depreciation expense of $2.9 million,&nbsp;&nbsp;offset by non-cash charges to income including $4.2 million in distributions from unconsolidated joint ventures, $2.9 million related to the loss from early extinguishment of debt, $24.3 million for a gain recognized on the contribution of previously owned freestanding facilities to the joint venture with UCHealth, an increase of $9.8 million in the earnings of unconsolidated joint ventures, and an increase of $9.1 million for a deferred tax benefit. Cash from operating activities had a decline in working capital items of approximately $36.8 million,&nbsp;&nbsp;primarily due to the increase in receivables compared to prior year
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	, c
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	ash outflows related to labor costs on new facilities where revenue is ramping up, equipment lease costs associated with the new facilities
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	and
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	new facility preopening expenses and marketing expenses
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	Net cash used in operating activities increased by $31.6&nbsp;million to $24.7&nbsp;million for the year ended December 31, 2014, from $6.9&nbsp;million provided by operating activities for the same period in 2013.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	This increase was primarily attributable to labor costs on new facilities where revenue is ramping up, corporate labor cost associated with expanding our management team in anticipation of new facility growth, equipment lease costs associated with the new facilities, new facility preopening expenses, marketing expenses, increases in accounts receivable balances due to increased revenues, restricted cash requirements related to the MPT Agreements and interest
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	.
</FONT>

<DIV STYLE="MARGIN-LEFT:10.2941176470588%;MARGIN-RIGHT:10.2941176470588%;">
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT 36PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	Net Cash from Investing Activities
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	Net cash used in investing activities decreased by $44.1&nbsp;million to $5.3&nbsp;million for the year ended December 31, 2015, from $49.4&nbsp;million for the same period in 2014. This decrease was primarily attributable to capital expenditures for construction of new facilities in prior year which did not recur in current year as we shifted toward third-party developers to fund all new construction.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	Net cash used in investing activities increased by $4.8&nbsp;million to $49.4&nbsp;million for the year ended December 31, 2014, from $44.6&nbsp;million for the same period in 2013. This increase was primarily attributable to capital expenditures for construction of new facilities.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT 36PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	Net Cash from Financing Activities
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	Net cash provided by financing activities decreased&nbsp;&nbsp;by $58.4&nbsp;million to $6.3&nbsp;million for the year ended December 31, 2015, from $64.7&nbsp;million for the same period in 2014. This decrease was primarily attributable to proceeds received in prior year from the initial public offering, net of transaction expenses of $96.2 million, offset by $60.0 million for the payment of a dividend to our then-existing owners which did not recur in the current year.&nbsp;&nbsp;We also experienced a decrease of $13.4 million in net borrowings under our Senior Secured Credit Facility used in prior year to finance construction of new facilities and a decrease of $0.2 million in the proceeds from an original owner prior to the initial public offering, which was offset by increases of $4.9 million in payments related to deferred loan costs incurred on the New Facility and capital lease payments, $3.5 million in tax distribution payments to LLC Unit holders and $0.2 million related to withholding requirements on the vesting of restricted Class A shares.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	Net cash provided by financing activities increased by $18.8&nbsp;million to $64.7&nbsp;million for the year ended December 31, 2014, from $45.8&nbsp;million for the same period in 2013. This increase was primarily attributable to proceeds from the initial public offering, net of transaction expenses of $96.2 million, offset by $60.0 million for the payment of a dividend to our then-existing owners prior to our initial public offering, a decrease of $22.1 million over the same period in prior year in borrowings under our Senior Secured Credit Facility to finance construction of new facilities, a decrease of $4.0 million in payments related to deferred loan costs that did not recur in 2014 and an increase of $0.5 million in payments to terminate an interest rate swap agreement in 2013.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	Off Balance Sheet Arrangements
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	During the periods presented, we did not have any relationships with unconsolidated entities or financial partnerships, such as entities often referred to as structured finance or special purpose entities, which would have been established for the purpose of facilitating off-balance sheet arrangements or other contractually narrow or limited purpose arrangements. We lease certain medical facilities and equipment under various non-cancelable operating leases. See "&#x2014;Obligations and Commitments&#x2014;Operating Lease Obligations."
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	As a result of our strategy of partnering with leading healthcare providers, we do not own a controlling interest in our facilities in Colorado and Arizona. At December 31, 2015, we accounted for these joint ventures under the equity method.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Our ownership percentage is 49.9% in each joint venture at December 31, 2015.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	As described above, our unconsolidated
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	joint ventur
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	es are
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	structured
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	as limited liability corporations.&nbsp;&nbsp;These joint ventures do not provide financing, liquidity, or market or credit risk support for us
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
</FONT>

<TD ALIGN="LEFT" VALIGN="TOP">
<P STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;MARGIN:0PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	Includes amounts representing interest
</FONT>
</P>

</DIV>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:12PT 0PT 12PT 36PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	Senior Secured Credit Facility
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	On October&nbsp;31, 2013, we entered into a Senior Secured Credit Facility (the &#x201C;Facility&#x201D;) for a $75.0&nbsp;million term loan, which matures on October&nbsp;31, 2018. The Facility includes an additional $165.0&nbsp;million delayed draw term loan commitment, which
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	expired in April 2015 and a $10.0&nbsp;million revolving commitment that matures on October&nbsp;31, 2018. All of our assets are pledged as collateral under the Senior Secured Credit Facility.&nbsp;&nbsp;Borrowings under the Facility are used by us to provide financing for working capital and capital expenditures for new facility expansion and replaced an existing credit facility.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	On March&nbsp;31, 2014, we amended the Facility to, among other things, increase the maximum aggregate amount permitted to be funded by Medical Properties Trust (&#x201C;MPT&#x201D;) under the MPT Agreements (as defined below) to $250.0 million.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	On June&nbsp;11, 2014, we entered into a second amendment to the Facility to, among other things, provide for a delayed draw term loan in an aggregate principal amount of up to $75.0 million, up to $60.0 million of which will be used to make specified distributions and up to $10.0 million to repay certain revolving loans.&nbsp;&nbsp;On June 11, 2014, we drew $75.0 million and made the $60.0 million dividend distribution on June 24, 2014. In April 2015, we drew $30.0 million on the delayed draw term loan prior to its expiration.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	On April 20, 2015, we amended the Facility to, among other things, increase the maximum aggregate amount permitted to be funded by MPT under the MPT Agreements to $500.0 million.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	Borrowings under the Facility bear interest, at our option, at a rate equal to an applicable margin over (a)&nbsp;a base rate determined by reference to the highest of (1)&nbsp;the prime rate, (2)&nbsp;the federal funds effective rate plus 0.50% and (3)&nbsp;LIBOR for an interest period of one month plus 1%, or (b)&nbsp;LIBOR for the applicable interest period. The margin for the Facility is 6.50% in the case of base rate loans and 7.50% in the case of LIBOR loans.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	The Facility includes an unused line fee of 0.50% per annum on the revolving commitment and delayed draw term loan commitment, a draw fee of 1.0% of the principal amount of each borrowing on the delayed draw term loan and an annual Agency fee of $0.1&nbsp;million. The Company repaid the total outstanding balance in October 2015.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	On October 6, 2015, the Company entered into a new Senior Secured Credit Facility (the &#x201C;New Facility&#x201D;) for a $125.0 million term loan and a $50.0 million revolving facility. The New Facility matures on October 6, 2020. The revolving credit facility includes a sub-limit of $15.0 million for letters of credit and a sub-limit of $5.0 million for swing line loans. In addition, the New Facility contains an option to borrow up to an additional $50.0 million under certain conditions. All of the assets of the Company&#x2019;s subsidiaries are pledged as collateral under the New Facility, and such subsidiaries guarantee the New Facility. Borrowings under the New Facility replace the Company&#x2019;s existing credit facility and will be used by the Company to provide financing for working capital and capital expenditures.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	Borrowings under the New Facility bear interest, at our option, at a rate equal to an applicable margin over (a) a base rate determined by reference to the highest of (1) the prime rate, (2) the federal funds effective rate plus 0.50% and (3) LIBOR for an interest period of one month plus 1%, or (b) LIBOR for the applicable interest period. The applicable
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
</FONT>
</P>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="MARGIN-LEFT:10.2941176470588%;MARGIN-RIGHT:10.2941176470588%;">
<P>
<FONT SIZE="1">
</FONT>
</P>
<DIV STYLE="WIDTH:100%">

<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	73

<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">

<DIV STYLE="WIDTH:100%">
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 6PT;COLOR:#0563C1;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">

<DIV STYLE="MARGIN-LEFT:10.2941176470588%;MARGIN-RIGHT:10.2941176470588%;">
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	margin for the New Facility ranges, based on our consolidated net leverage ratio, from 2.25% to 3.00% in the case of base rate loans and from 3.25% to 4.00% in the case of LIBOR loans. The New Facility includes an unused line fee ranging, based on our consolidated net leverage ratio, from 0.40% to 0.50% per annum on the revolving commitment. We had $39.8 million available under the revolving commitment at December 31, 2015, subject to certain debt covenants.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	The
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	New
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	Facility contains a number of significant negative covenants. Such negative covenants, among other things and subject to certain exceptions, restrict
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	Adeptus Health Inc.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	and its subsidiaries&#x2019; ability to incur additional indebtedness, make guarantees and enter into hedging agreements; create liens on assets; engage in mergers or consolidations; transfer assets; pay dividends and distributions; change the nature of our business; make investments, loans and advances, including acquisitions; engage in certain transactions with affiliates; amend certain material agreements, including the MPT Agreements and organizational documents; enter into certain joint ventures; enter into certain restrictive agreements; and make certain changes to our accounting practices.&nbsp;&nbsp;In addition, the
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	New
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	Facility contains financial covenants that, among other things, require us to maintain a consolidated
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	net
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	leverage ratio of at most 5.00 to 1.00
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	as of December 31, 2015
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	(decreasing to 2.00 to 1.00
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	as of September
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	30, 20
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	19
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	); a consolidated fixed charge coverage ratio of at least 1.25 to 1.00; and a minimum Non-MPT Facility EBITDA as of the end of any fiscal quarter
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	of not
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	less than $40 million
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	.&nbsp;&nbsp;The financial covenant calculations are based on
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	Adeptus Health Inc.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	and its subsidiaries as a consolidated group. In addition, the
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	New
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	Facility includes certain limitations on intercompany indebtedness.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	The affirmative covenants, negative covenants, and financial covenants, are measured on a quarterly basis and, as of December 31, 2015, we were in compliance with all covenant requirements.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT 36PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	Capital Lease Obligations
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	Assets under capital leases totaled approximately
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	$4.2
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&nbsp;million as of December 31, 2015, and were included within the buildings component of net property and equipment. Accumulated amortization associated with these capital lease assets totaled
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	approximately $0.6&nbsp;million for
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	the year ended December 31, 2015.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	Assets under capital leases totaled approximately $4.2&nbsp;million as of December&nbsp;31, 2014, and were included within buildings, computer equipment, medical equipment, office equipment and automobiles. Accumulated amortization associated with these capital lease assets totaled approximately $0.3 million for the year ended December&nbsp;31, 2014.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT 36PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	Operating Lease Obligations
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	We lease certain medical facilities and equipment under various non-cancelable operating leases. In June 2013, we entered into a Master Funding and Development Agreement (the &#x201C;Initial MPT Agreement&#x201D;) with an affiliate of Medical Properties Trust (&#x201C;MPT) to fund future facilities.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	Pursuant to the Initial MPT Agreement, MPT will acquire parcels of land, fund the ground-up construction of new freestanding emergency room facilities and lease the facilities to us upon completion of construction. Under the terms of the agreement, MPT is required to fund all hard and soft costs, including the project purchase price, closing costs and pursuit costs for the assets relating to the construction of
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	up to 25 facilities with a maximum aggregate funding of $100.0&nbsp;million. The maximum aggregate funding has been met.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	The Additional MPT Agreement allows a maximum aggregate funding of $150.0 million, of which $201.7 million remained available as of December 31, 2015.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	All other material terms remain consistent with the Initial MPT Agreement. Each
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	completed project will be leased for an initial term of 15&nbsp;years, with three five-year renewal options. We follow the guidance in Accounting Standards Codification, or ASC, 840,
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	Leases
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	, and ASC 810,
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	Consolidation
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	, in evaluating the lease as a build-to-suit lease transaction to determine whether we would be considered the accounting owner of the facilities during the construction period. In applying the accounting guidance, we concluded that one facility completed in 2013 under this arrangement qualified for capitalization.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:12PT 0PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	In July 2014, the Company entered into an additional Master Funding and Development Agreement
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	(the &#x201C;Additional MPT Agreement&#x201D; and, together with the Initial MPT Agreement, the &#x201C;MPT Agreements&#x201D;)
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	with MPT to fund future
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	new freestanding emergency rooms and hospitals
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	. This agreement is separate from and in addition to the
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
</FONT>
</P>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="MARGIN-LEFT:10.2941176470588%;MARGIN-RIGHT:10.2941176470588%;">
<P>
<FONT SIZE="1">
</FONT>
</P>
<DIV STYLE="WIDTH:100%">
<P STYLE="MARGIN:24PT 0PT 0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:CENTER;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	74
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
</FONT>
</P>

<DIV STYLE="MARGIN-LEFT:10.2941176470588%;MARGIN-RIGHT:10.2941176470588%;">
<P STYLE="MARGIN:12PT 0PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	Company&#x2019;s
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	Initial
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	MPT Agreement. The
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	Additional MPT
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	A
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	greement allows for an additional maximum aggregate funding of
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	$150.0
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	million. All other material terms remain consistent with the
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	Initial
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	MPT Agreement.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	On April 20, 2015, the Company entered into an amendment to the Additional MPT Agreement which adds an additional aggregate funding of $250.0 million, increasing the maximum aggregate funding under all of the MPT Agreements to $500.0 million. All newly constructed facilities under the MPT Agreements will have initial terms of 15 years, with three five-year renewal options.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	In addition to the MPT Agreements, the Company has entered into similar agreements with certain developers to fund and lead the development efforts on the construction of future facilities. As of December 31, 2015, the Company had total receivables
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	of $12.2
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	million from the lessor to the MPT Agreements and certain developers for soft costs incurred for facilities currently under development.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	We lease approximately 80,000 square feet for our corporate headquarters. Lease expense associated with this lease was $1.6&nbsp;million for the year ended December&nbsp;31,&nbsp;2015.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	We have
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	sublease agreements with the joint ventures in Arizona and Colorado, under which the Company subleases certain freestanding emergency room facilities, ground leases and equipment leases to the joint ventures.&nbsp;&nbsp;Under these agreements, the Company received
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	$10.8
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	million and
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	$0.4
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	million during the
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	years
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	ended
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	December
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&nbsp;3
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	1, 2015 and 2014,
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	respectively, as rental income which is accounted for as a reduction of rent expense
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	Capital Expenditures
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	Our current plans for our business contemplate capital expenditures to expand our operations. The MPT Agreements will be used to fund a significant portion of our new facilities. We typically incur approximately $0.2&nbsp;million in capital expenditures related to each MPT-funded facility. Facilities funded under the MPT Agreements will be operating leases and thus not considered a capital expenditure.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">

	):
</FONT>
</P>
