<P STYLE="PAGE-BREAK-AFTER:ALWAYS">
	&nbsp;
</P>
<A NAME="eolPage94"></A>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="MARGIN-LEFT:10.2941176470588%;MARGIN-RIGHT:10.2941176470588%;">
<DIV STYLE="WIDTH:100%">
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 30PT;COLOR:#0563C1;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<A HREF="#ADPT-20151231X10K_HTM_TOC">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#0563C1;">
	Table of Contents
</FONT>
</A>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 6PT;TEXT-ALIGN:CENTER;COLOR:#000000;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;COLOR:#000000;">
	Adeptus Health Inc. and Subsidiaries
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 6PT;TEXT-ALIGN:CENTER;COLOR:#000000;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;COLOR:#000000;">
	NOTES TO CONSOLIDATED FINANCIAL STATEMENTS
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 6PT;TEXT-ALIGN:CENTER;COLOR:#000000;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
	&nbsp;
</P>
</DIV>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="MARGIN-LEFT:10.2941176470588%;MARGIN-RIGHT:10.2941176470588%;">
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	To the extent that the Company's assessment of such tax position changes, the change in estimate is recorded in the period in which the determination is made. The Company reports tax related interest and penalties as a component of the provision for income tax and operating expenses, respectively, if applicable. The Company has not recognized any uncertain tax positions.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;TEXT-DECORATION:UNDERLINE;">
	Deferred Rent
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	The Company records rent expense for operating leases on a straight-line basis over the life of the related leases. The Company has certain facility and equipment leases that allow for leasehold improvements allowance, free rent, and escalating rental payments. Straight-line expenses that are greater than the actual amount paid are recorded as deferred rent and amortized over the life of the lease.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;TEXT-DECORATION:UNDERLINE;">
	Variable Interest Entities
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;TEXT-INDENT:27PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	The Company follows the guidance in ASC 810-10-15-14 in order to determine
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	if we are the primary beneficiary of a variable interest entity (&#x201C;VIE&#x201D;) for financial reporting purposes.&nbsp;&nbsp;We consider whether we have the power to direct the activities of the VIE that most significantly impact the economic performance of the VIE and whether we have the obligation to absorb losses or the right to receive returns that would be significant to the VIE. We consolidate a VIE when we are the primary beneficiary of the VIE. At December 31, 2015, the Company determined that it has
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	one
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	joint venture interest which it considers a VIE for which it is not the primary beneficiary.&nbsp;&nbsp;Accordingly, we account for this investment in joint venture using the equity method.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;TEXT-DECORATION:UNDERLINE;">
	Investment in Unconsolidated Joint Ventures
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:4.5PT 0PT 0PT;TEXT-INDENT:24.5PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	Investments in unconsolidated companies in which the Company exerts significant influence but does not control or otherwise consolidate are accounted for using the equity method. As of December 30, 2015, the Company accounted for
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	15
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	freestanding facilities associated with our joint venture with University of Colorado Health and our Arizona hospital and its
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	four
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	freestanding departments associated with our joint venture with Dignity Health using the equity method. The Company has an ownership interest of
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	49.9%
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	in each joint venture.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:9PT 0PT 0PT;TEXT-INDENT:24.5PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	These investments are included as investment in unconsolidated joint ventures in the accompanying consolidated balance sheets.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:24.5PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:24.5PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	Equity in earnings of unconsolidated joint ventures consists of (i) the Company&#x2019;s share of the income (loss) generated from its non-controlling equity investment in
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	one
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	full-service healthcare hospital facility and four freestanding emergency rooms in Arizona, and (ii) the Company&#x2019;s preferred return and its share of the income (loss) generated from its non-controlling equity investment in
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	15
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	freestanding emergency rooms in Colorado. Because the operations are central to the Company&#x2019;s business strategy, equity in earnings of unconsolidated joint ventures is classified as a component of operating income in the accompanying consolidated statements of operations. The Company has contracts to manage the facilities, which results in the Company having an active role in the operations of the facilities and devoting a significant portion of its corporate resources to the fulfillment of these management responsibilities.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;TEXT-DECORATION:UNDERLINE;">
	Recent Accounting Pronouncements
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	In May 2014, the FASB issued ASU No. 2014-09,
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	Revenue from Contracts with Customers (Topic 606)
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	, which requires an entity to recognize the amount of revenue to which it expects to be entitled for the transfer of promised goods or services to customers. The ASU will replace most existing revenue recognition guidance in U.S. GAAP when it becomes effective. The new standard will become effective for the Company on January 1, 2018. Early application is permitted to the original effective date of January 1, 2017. The standard permits the use of either the retrospective or cumulative effect transition method. The Company is evaluating the effect that ASU 2014-09 will have on its
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
</FONT>
</P>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="MARGIN-LEFT:10.2941176470588%;MARGIN-RIGHT:10.2941176470588%;">
<P>
<FONT SIZE="1">
</FONT>
</P>
<DIV STYLE="WIDTH:100%">
<P STYLE="MARGIN:24PT 0PT 0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:CENTER;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	94
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
</FONT>
</P>
</DIV>

<DIV STYLE="MARGIN-LEFT:10.2941176470588%;MARGIN-RIGHT:10.2941176470588%;">
<HR ALIGN="CENTER" STYLE='BACKGROUND-COLOR:#000000; BORDER-WIDTH:0; COLOR:#000000; HEIGHT:2PT; LINEHEIGHT:0; WIDTH:100%;'>

	&nbsp;

<A NAME="eolPage95"></A>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="MARGIN-LEFT:10.2941176470588%;MARGIN-RIGHT:10.2941176470588%;">
<DIV STYLE="WIDTH:100%">
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 30PT;COLOR:#0563C1;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<A HREF="#ADPT-20151231X10K_HTM_TOC">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#0563C1;">
	Table of Contents
</FONT>
</A>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 6PT;TEXT-ALIGN:CENTER;COLOR:#000000;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;COLOR:#000000;">
	Adeptus Health Inc. and Subsidiaries
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 6PT;TEXT-ALIGN:CENTER;COLOR:#000000;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;COLOR:#000000;">
	NOTES TO CONSOLIDATED FINANCIAL STATEMENTS
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 6PT;TEXT-ALIGN:CENTER;COLOR:#000000;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
	&nbsp;
</P>
</DIV>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="MARGIN-LEFT:10.2941176470588%;MARGIN-RIGHT:10.2941176470588%;">
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	consolidated financial statements and related disclosures. The Company has not yet selected a transition method nor has it determined the effect of the standard on its ongoing financial reporting.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	In February 2015, the FASB issued ASU No. 2015-02, &#x201C;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	Consolidation: Amendments to the Consolidation Analysis&#x201D; (Topic 810)
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	. This standard modifies existing consolidation guidance for reporting organizations that are required to evaluate whether they should consolidate certain legal entities. ASU 2015-02 is effective for fiscal years and interim periods within those years beginning after December 15, 2015 and requires either a retrospective or a modified retrospective approach to adoption. Early adoption is permitted.&nbsp;&nbsp;We are currently evaluating the potential impact of this standard on our consolidated financial position, results of operations and cash flows.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	In April 2015, the FASB issued ASU No. 2015-03,
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	"Simplifying the Presentation of Debt Issuance Costs"
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	(Subtopic 835-30)
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	, which changes the presentation of debt issuance costs in financial statements. ASU No. 2015-03 requires an entity to present such costs in the balance sheet as a direct deduction from the related debt liability rather than as an asset. Amortization of the costs will continue to be reported as interest expense. ASU No. 2015-03 is effective for annual reporting periods beginning after December 15, 2015. Early adoption is permitted. The new guidance will be applied retrospectively to each prior period presented. The Company will implement the provisions of ASU 2015-03 as of January 1, 2016.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	In November 2015, the FASB issued ASU No. 2015-17, &#x201C;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	Income Taxes (Topic 740): Balance Sheet Classification of Deferred Taxes
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#x201D;, which amended the balance sheet classification requirements for deferred income taxes to simplify their presentation in the statement of financial position. The ASU requires that deferred tax liabilities and assets be classified as noncurrent in a classified statement of financial position. This ASU is effective for fiscal years beginning after December 31, 2016, with early adoption permitted. The Company early adopted the provisions of this ASU for the presentation and classification of its deferred tax assets at December 31, 2015 and has reflected the change on the consolidated balance sheet for all periods presented.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:14.3PT 0PT 12PT;TEXT-INDENT:19.8PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	In February 2016, the FASB issued ASU No. 2016-02, &#x201C;Leases&#x201D; (Topic 842). This new standard establishes a comprehensive new lease accounting model.&nbsp;The new standard clarifies the definition of a lease, requires a dual approach to lease classification similar to current lease classifications, and causes lessees to recognize leases on the balance sheet as a lease liability with a corresponding right-of-use asset for leases with a lease term of more than twelve months. The standard is effective for interim and annual periods beginning after December 15, 2018. Early adoption is permitted. The new standard requires a modified retrospective transition for capital or operating leases existing at or entered into after the beginning of the earliest comparative period presented in the financial statements, but it does not require transition accounting for leases that expire prior to the date of initial application. We are evaluating the impact of the new standard on our consolidated financial statements.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:INHERIT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	We do not believe any other recently issued, but not yet effective, revisions to authoritative guidance will have a material effect on our condensed consolidated financial position, results of operations or cash flow
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	s.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
</FONT>

<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	NOTE 3&#x2014;PROPERTY AND EQUIPMENT
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	Property and equipment consisted of the following, as of December 31, 2015 and 2014 (
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	in thousands
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	):
</FONT>
</P>
<DIV STYLE="WIDTH:100%;">
<TABLE CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" ALIGN="CENTER" STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE;WIDTH: 80.00%;MARGIN-LEFT:0PT;">
<TR>
<TD VALIGN="BOTTOM" STYLE="WIDTH:68.28%;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;BORDER-LEFT:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;BORDER-RIGHT:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;BACKGROUND-COLOR: #AUTO;PADDING:0PT;">
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 0.05PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 1PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:1PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
</TD>
<TD VALIGN="BOTTOM" STYLE="WIDTH:02.32%;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;BORDER-LEFT:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;BORDER-RIGHT:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;BACKGROUND-COLOR: #AUTO;PADDING:0PT;">
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 0.05PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
	&nbsp;
</P>
</TD>
<TD VALIGN="BOTTOM" STYLE="WIDTH:02.32%;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;BORDER-LEFT:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;BORDER-RIGHT:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;BACKGROUND-COLOR: #AUTO;PADDING:0PT;">
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 0.05PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
	&nbsp;

<P STYLE="MARGIN:12PT 0PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	Assets under capital leases totaled approximately
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	$4.2
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&nbsp;million as of December 31, 2015 and 2014, respectively, and were included within the buildings component of net property and equipment. Accumulated depreciation associated with these capital lease assets totaled approximately
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	$0.6
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	million and
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	$0.3
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	million as of December 31, 2015 and 2014, respectively.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:12PT 0PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	NOTE 4&#x2014;INVESTMENT IN UNCONSOLIDATED JOINT VENTURES
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:12PT 0PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;TEXT-DECORATION:UNDERLINE;">
	Joint Venture with Dignity Health
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:12PT 0PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	On October 22, 2014, the Company announced its expansion into Arizona through a joint venture with Dignity Health, one of the nation&#x2019;s largest health systems. The partnership started with Dignity Health Arizona General Hospital, a full-service general hospital facility in Laveen, Arizona, and includes providing for additional access to emergency medical care in the Phoenix area. As of December 31, 2015, the joint venture with Dignity Health has four freestanding emergency departments in Arizona.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;TEXT-DECORATION:UNDERLINE;">
	Joint Venture with UCHealth
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:12PT 0PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	On April 21, 2015, the Company announced the formation of a joint venture with UCHealth to enhance access to emergency medical care in Colorado.&nbsp;&nbsp;The Company contributed the
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	12
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	existing freestanding emergency rooms it held in Colorado and the related business associated with these facilities to the joint venture.&nbsp;&nbsp;The contribution of the controlling interest in these facilities and their operations was deemed a change of control for accounting purposes, and as such, the Company has recorded a gain of
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	$24.3
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	million on the contribution of the previously fully owned facilities during the year ended December 31, 2015. As of December 31, 2015, the joint venture
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	had
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	15
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	freestanding
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	facilities under the UCHealth partnership.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:12PT 0PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	Pursuant to the terms of the joint venture agreement, the Company receives an annual preferred return up to a specified amount on its investment in the joint venture prior to proportionate distributions to the partners. Due to this preferred return provision within the joint venture agreement, this joint venture interest is considered a variable interest entity. Additional terms within the agreement allow for certain decisions to be made in which
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	the Company has
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	determined that
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	it does
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	not have control. As such,
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	the Company
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	concluded that
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	it is
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	not the primary beneficiary of the VIE.&nbsp;&nbsp;Accordingly,
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	the Company
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	accoun
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	ts
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	for this investment in joint venture under the equity method.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;TEXT-DECORATION:UNDERLINE;">
</FONT>
</P>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="MARGIN-LEFT:10.2941176470588%;MARGIN-RIGHT:10.2941176470588%;">

<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 6PT;TEXT-ALIGN:CENTER;COLOR:#000000;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;COLOR:#000000;">
	Adeptus Health Inc. and Subsidiaries
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 6PT;TEXT-ALIGN:CENTER;COLOR:#000000;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;COLOR:#000000;">
	NOTES TO CONSOLIDATED FINANCIAL STATEMENTS
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 6PT;TEXT-ALIGN:CENTER;COLOR:#000000;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
	&nbsp;
</P>
</DIV>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="MARGIN-LEFT:10.2941176470588%;MARGIN-RIGHT:10.2941176470588%;">
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;TEXT-DECORATION:UNDERLINE;">
	Joint Venture with Ochsner Health System
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:12PT 0PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	In September 2015, the Company announced the formation of a new partnership with New Orleans-based Ochsner Health System to enhance access to emergency medical care in Louisiana. The joint venture will include a hospital and multiple freestanding emergency departments in locations still to be determined. This joint venture did not have operations during the year ended December 31, 2015.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:12PT 0PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	The Company accounts for each of these joint ventures under the equity method of accounting as an investment in unconsolidated joint ventures, as the Company&#x2019;s level of influence is significant but does not reach the threshold of controlling the entity.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:12PT 0PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">

</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	):

<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	The Company used interest-rate-related derivative instruments to manage its exposure related to changes in interest rates on its variable-rate debt instruments. The Company does not enter into derivative instruments for any purpose other than cash flow hedging. The Company does not speculate using derivative instruments.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	By using derivative financial instruments to hedge exposures to changes in interest rates, the Company expose
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	s
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	itself to credit risk and market risk. Credit risk is the failure of the counterparty to perform under the terms of the derivative contract. When the fair value of a derivative contract is positive, the counterparty owes the Company, which creates credit risk for the Company. When the fair value of a derivative contract is negative, the Company owes the counterparty, and therefore, the Company is not exposed to the counterparty's credit risk in those circumstances. The Company minimizes counterparty credit risk in derivative instruments by entering into transactions with high-quality counterparties whose credit rating is higher than Aa. The derivative instruments entered into by the Company do not contain credit-risk-related contingent features.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	Market risk is the adverse effect on the value of a derivative instrument that results from a change in interest rates, currency exchange rates, or commodity prices. The market risk associated with interest-rate contracts is managed by establishing and monitoring parameters that limit the types and degree of market risk that may be undertaken.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	The Company assesses interest rate risk by continually identifying and monitoring changes in interest rate exposures that may adversely impact expected future cash flows and by evaluating hedging opportunities. The Company maintains risk management control systems to monitor interest rate risk attributable to both the Company's outstanding or forecasted debt obligations as well as the Company's offsetting hedge positions. The risk management control systems
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
</FONT>
</P>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="MARGIN-LEFT:10.2941176470588%;MARGIN-RIGHT:10.2941176470588%;">
<P>
<FONT SIZE="1">
</FONT>
</P>
<DIV STYLE="WIDTH:100%">
<P STYLE="MARGIN:24PT 0PT 0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:CENTER;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	98
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
</FONT>
</P>
</DIV>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="MARGIN-LEFT:10.2941176470588%;MARGIN-RIGHT:10.2941176470588%;">

<DIV STYLE="WIDTH:100%">
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 30PT;COLOR:#0563C1;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<A HREF="#ADPT-20151231X10K_HTM_TOC">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#0563C1;">
	Table of Contents
</FONT>
</A>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 6PT;TEXT-ALIGN:CENTER;COLOR:#000000;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;COLOR:#000000;">
	Adeptus Health Inc. and Subsidiaries
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 6PT;TEXT-ALIGN:CENTER;COLOR:#000000;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;COLOR:#000000;">
	NOTES TO CONSOLIDATED FINANCIAL STATEMENTS
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 6PT;TEXT-ALIGN:CENTER;COLOR:#000000;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
	&nbsp;
</P>
</DIV>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="MARGIN-LEFT:10.2941176470588%;MARGIN-RIGHT:10.2941176470588%;">
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	involve the use of analytical techniques, including cash flow sensitivity analysis, to estimate the expected impact of changes in interest rates on the Company's future cash flows.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	Changes in the fair value of interest rate swaps and cap agreements designated as hedging instruments that effectively offset the variability of cash flows associated with variable-rate, long-term debt obligations are reported in accumulated other comprehensive income. These amounts subsequently are reclassified into interest expense as a yield adjustment of the hedged interest payments in the same period in which the related interest affects earnings.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	In May 2012, the Company entered into a forward interest rate swap agreement with a notional amount of
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	$24.0
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&nbsp;million to manage exposure to changes in interest rates associated with its variable interest rate debt. This agreement had the economic effect of modifying the LIBOR variable component of the Company's interest rate on an equivalent amount of the Company's Term Loan to a fixed rate of
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	1.20%
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	. This swap agreement was not designated by the Company as a hedge as of December 31, 2013. The Company did not utilize the swap agreement until April&nbsp;30, 2013. The Company recognized a loss of approximately
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	$0.1
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	million for the year ended December 31, 2013 on the change in fair value of the swap agreement, which is included as a component of other (expense) income within the consolidated statements of operations.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	As of December 31, 2015, the Company maintained
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	one
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	interest rate cap agreement with notional amount totaling
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	$37.5
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&nbsp;million. This agreement has the economic effect of capping the LIBOR variable component of the Company's interest rate at a maximum of
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	3.00%
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	on an equivalent amount of the Company's Term Loan debt. The cap agreement does not contain credit-risk contingent features. In October 2015, the Company extinguished the debt related to the existing Credit Facility, and reclassified losses of
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	$0.1
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	million from accumulated other comprehensive income into earnings. The interest rate cap agreement was terminated on January 4, 2016.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">

<P STYLE="MARGIN:12PT 0PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	On October&nbsp;31, 2013, the Company entered into a Senior Secured Credit Facility (the &#x201C;Facility&#x201D;) for a
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	$75.0
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&nbsp;million term loan which matures on October&nbsp;31, 2018. The Facility includes an additional
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	$165.0
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&nbsp;million delayed draw term loan commitment, which expired in April 2015, and a
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	$10.0
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&nbsp;million revolving commitment that matures on October&nbsp;31, 2018. All of the Company's assets are pledged as collateral under the Facility. The borrowing under the Facility is used by the Company to provide financing for working capital, capital expenditures and for new facility expansion and replaced an existing credit facility.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	On March&nbsp;31, 2014, the Company amended the Facility to, among other things, increase the maximum aggregate amount permitted to be funded by Medical Properties Trust (&#x201C;MPT&#x201D;) under the MPT Agreements to
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	$250.0
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	million. See Note 11 (
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	Commitments and Contingencies
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	) for more information.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	On June&nbsp;11, 2014, the Company entered into a second amendment to the Facility to, among other things, provide for a borrowing under the delayed draw term loan in an aggregate principal amount of up to
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	$75.0
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	million, up to
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	$60.0
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	million in principal amount of which will be used to make specified distributions and up to
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	$10.0
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	million in principal amount of which will be used to repay certain revolving loans.&nbsp;&nbsp;On June 11, 2014, the Company drew
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	$75.0
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	million and made the
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	$60.0
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	million dividend distribution on June 24, 2014.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	On April 20, 2015, the Company amended the Facility to, among other things, increase the maximum aggregate amount permitted to be funded by MPT under the MPT Agreements to $500.0 million.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	Borrowings under the Facility bear interest, at our option, at a rate equal to an applicable margin over (a)&nbsp;a base rate determined by reference to the highest of (1)&nbsp;the
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	prime rate
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	, (2)&nbsp;the
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	federal funds
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	effective rate plus
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	0.50%
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	and (3)&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	LIBOR
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	for an interest period of one month plus
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	1%
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	, or (b)&nbsp;LIBOR for the applicable interest period. The margin for the Facility is
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	6.50%
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	in the case of base rate loans and
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	7.50%
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	in the case of LIBOR loans.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	The Facility includes an unused line fee of
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	0.50%
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	per annum on the revolving commitment and delayed draw term loan commitment, a draw fee of
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	1.0%
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	of the principal amount of each borrowing on the delayed draw term loan and an annual Agency fee of
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	$0.1
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&nbsp;million. In April 2015, the Company drew
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	$30.0
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	million on the delayed draw term loan prior to its expiration. At December 31, 2014, the Company had
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	$80.2
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&nbsp;million available under the delayed draw term commitment, and&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	$4.0
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&nbsp;million available under the revolving commitment, respectively.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	On October 6, 2015, the Company entered into a senior secured credit facility (the &#x201C;New Facility&#x201D;) for a
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	$125.0
</FONT>

</FONT>

</FONT>

</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	$15.0
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	million for letters of credit and a sub-limit of
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	$5.0
</FONT>

	million for swing line loans. In addition, the New Facility contains an option to borrow up to an additional
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	$50.0
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	million under certain conditions. All of the assets of the Company&#x2019;s subsidiaries are pledged as collateral under the New Facility, and such
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
</FONT>

<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;COLOR:#000000;">
	Adeptus Health Inc. and Subsidiaries
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 6PT;TEXT-ALIGN:CENTER;COLOR:#000000;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;COLOR:#000000;">
	NOTES TO CONSOLIDATED FINANCIAL STATEMENTS
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 6PT;TEXT-ALIGN:CENTER;COLOR:#000000;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
	&nbsp;
</P>
</DIV>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="MARGIN-LEFT:10.2941176470588%;MARGIN-RIGHT:10.2941176470588%;">
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	subsidiaries guarantee the New Facility. Borrowings under the New Facility replace the Company&#x2019;s existing credit facility and will be used by the Company to provide financing for working capital and capital expenditures.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	Borrowings under the New Facility bear interest, at our option, at a rate equal to an applicable margin over (a) a base rate determined by reference to the highest of (1) the prime rate, (2) the federal funds effective rate plus
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	0.50%
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	and (3) LIBOR for an interest period of one month plus
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	1%
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	, or (b) LIBOR for the applicable interest period. The applicable margin for the New Facility ranges, based on our consolidated net leverage ratio, from
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	2.25%
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	to
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	3.00%
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	in the case of base rate loans and from
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	3.25%
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	to
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	4.00%
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	in the case of LIBOR loans. The New Facility includes an unused line fee ranging, based on our consolidated net leverage ratio, from
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	0.40%
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	to
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	0.50%
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	per annum on the revolving commitment. The Company had
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	$39.8
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	million available under the revolving commitment at December 31, 2015.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">

	The Facility contains certain affirmative covenants, negative covenants, and financial covenants which are measured on a quarterly basis. As of December 31, 2015, the Company was in compliance with all covenant requirements. In conjunction with entering into the New Facility, the Company incurred a
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	$5.0
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	million loss, consisting of a prepayment premium of
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	$2.1
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	million and write off of deferred loan costs of
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	$2.9
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	million, on the extinguishment of debt related to previously capitalized costs from its previous debt agreements.
</FONT>
</P>

</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&nbsp;

<P STYLE="MARGIN:12PT 0PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	The Company leases certain medical facilities and equipment under various noncancelable operating leases. In June 2013, the Company entered into
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	an
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	initial
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	MPT Agreement
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	(the &#x201C;Initial MPT Agreement&#x201D;)
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	with
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	an affiliate of Medical Properties Trust (&#x201C;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	MPT
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#x201D;)
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	to fund future facilit
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	y development and construction
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	. The lessor to the MPT Agreement will acquire parcels of land, fund the ground-up construction of new freestanding emergency room facilities and lease the facilities to the Company upon completion of construction. Under the terms of the agreement, the lessor is to fund all hard and soft costs, including the project purchase price, closing costs and pursuit costs for the assets relating to the construction of up to
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	twenty-five
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	facilities with a maximum aggregate funding of
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	$100.0
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&nbsp;million. Each completed project will be leased for an initial term of
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	15
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&nbsp;years, with
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	three
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	5
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	-year renewal options. The Company follows the guidance in ASC 840,
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	Leases
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	, and ASC 810,
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	Consolidation,
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	in evaluating the lease as a build-to-suit lease transaction to determine whether the Company would be considered the accounting owner of the facilities during the construction period.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	In applying the accounting guidance, the Company concluded that the
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	one
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	facility completed in 2013 under this arrangement qualified for capitalization.

<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	NOTE 13&#x2014;STOCK BASED COMPENSATION
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	In connection with the initial public offering, the Company&#x2019;s Board of Directors adopted the Adeptus Health Inc. 2014 Omnibus Incentive Plan (the &#x201C;2014 Plan&#x201D;). The Omnibus Incentive Plan provides for the granting of stock options, restricted stock and other stock-based or performance-based awards to directors, officers, employees, consultants and advisors of the Company and its affiliates. The total number of shares of Class A common stock that may be issued under the Omnibus Incentive Plan is
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	1,033,500
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	On June 24, 2014, the Company granted
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	11,934
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	restricted Class A shares to its non-employee directors under the Omnibus Incentive Plan, representing the prorated amount of the directors&#x2019; annual equity award for fiscal 2014. These restricted shares vested on January 1, 2015. In July 2014, the Company granted to certain employees
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	35,856
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	restricted Class A shares, which vest over
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	4
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	years. For the year ended December 31, 2015, the Company granted
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	149,741
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	restricted Class A shares to certain employees and non-employee directors, which vest over
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	6
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	months to
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	4
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	years. The weighted average grant date-fair value of restricted Class A shares granted during the years ended December 31, 2015 and 2014 was
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	$37.10
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	and
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	$24.33
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	per share, respectively. At December 31, 2015, 1
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	70
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	,
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	521
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	of these restricted Class A shares remained unvested. Compensation expense for time-based restricted share awards is recognized over the vesting period on a straight-line basis, adjusted for estimated forfeitures.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	The 2014 Plan allowed for the grant of incentive stock options intended to qualify under Section 422 of the Internal Revenue Code (the &#x201C;IRC&#x201D;).&nbsp;&nbsp;The Company granted
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	30,000
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	stock options with an exercise price of
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	$86.80
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	, which vest quarterly over
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	three
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	years and expire
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	ten
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	years from the date of grant. All outstanding stock options were unvested as of December 31, 2015.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
</FONT>
</P>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="MARGIN-LEFT:10.2941176470588%;MARGIN-RIGHT:10.2941176470588%;">
<P>
<FONT SIZE="1">
</FONT>

<DIV STYLE="WIDTH:100%">
<P STYLE="MARGIN:24PT 0PT 0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:CENTER;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">

	104

<DIV STYLE="WIDTH:100%">
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 30PT;COLOR:#0563C1;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<A HREF="#ADPT-20151231X10K_HTM_TOC">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#0563C1;">
	Table of Contents
</FONT>
</A>

<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 6PT;TEXT-ALIGN:CENTER;COLOR:#000000;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;COLOR:#000000;">
	Adeptus Health Inc. and Subsidiaries
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 6PT;TEXT-ALIGN:CENTER;COLOR:#000000;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;COLOR:#000000;">
	NOTES TO CONSOLIDATED FINANCIAL STATEMENTS
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 6PT;TEXT-ALIGN:CENTER;COLOR:#000000;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
	&nbsp;
</P>
</DIV>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="MARGIN-LEFT:10.2941176470588%;MARGIN-RIGHT:10.2941176470588%;">
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	As of December 31, 2015, there was
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	$4.7
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	million of unrecognized stock-based compensation expense related to outstanding unvested restricted Class A shares and stock option awards. That cost is expected to be recognized over a weighted average period of
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	2.0
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	years.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	The Company also has one legacy equity-compensation plan, under which it has issued agreements awarding incentive units (restricted units) in the Company to certain employees and non-employee directors. In conjunction with the Reorganization Transactions, these restricted units were replaced with LLC Units with consistent restrictive terms. The restricted units are subject to such conditions as continued employment, passage of time and/or satisfaction of performance criteria as specified in the agreements. The restricted units vest over
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	3
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	to
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	4
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&nbsp;years from the date of grant. The Company used a waterfall calculation, based on the capital structure and payout of each class of debt and equity, and a present value pricing model less marketability discount to determine the fair values of the restricted units. The assumptions used in the price simulation model for units granted during 2013 include risk-free interest rates of
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	0.93%
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	, volatility of
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	25.0%
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	and a dividend rate of
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	0%
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	. The weighted average fair value of incentive units granted during the year ended December 31, 2013 was
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	$1,262
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	and
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	$384
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	for the time-based and performance based units, respectively. The assumptions used for the 2012 incentive units included a risk-free interest rate of
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	0.72%
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	, volatility of
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	30.0%
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	and a dividend yield of
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	0%
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	. The weighted average fair value of incentive units granted during 2012 was
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	$204
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	and
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	$37
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	for the time-based and performance based units, respectively. The Company has not issued any incentive units under the legacy plan since 2013.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	The Company recorded compensation expense of
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	$2.7
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&nbsp;million,
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	$1.0
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	million, and
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	$0.6
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	million, adjusted for forfeitures, during the years ended December 31, 2015, 2014 and 2013, respectively, related to restricted units and stock options with time-based vesting schedules. Compensation expense for the value of the portion of the time-based restricted unit that is ultimately expected to vest is recognized using a straight-line method over the vesting period, adjusted for forfeitures. On February 18, 2015, our Board of Directors accelerated the vesting of all performance based units.&nbsp;&nbsp;As a result of the acceleration, the Company recognized
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	$0.1
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	million of additional stock-based compensation expense for the year ended December 31, 2015.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 1PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:1PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>

<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	Prior to the Reorganization, we were not a federal taxpayer.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	The Company&#x2019;s effective tax rate for the period differs from the statutory rates due primarily to state taxes that are not based on pre-tax income/(loss) but on gross margin resulting in state tax expense
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	with little relation to pre-tax income
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	even in periods of pretax losses
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:INHERIT;">
	.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	Our management evaluates the realizability of the deferred tax assets and determines whether it is more likely than not that the deferred tax assets are realizable. We consider whether a valuation allowance is needed on our deferred tax assets by evaluating all positive and negative evidence relative to our ability to recover deferred tax assets, including scheduled reversals of deferred tax liabilities, projected future taxable income, tax planning strategies and recent financial operations. During 2014, we were able to conclude that given our performance, the forecast of future income
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	and
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	the realization of our deferred tax asset was more likely than not
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	. As such, we
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	did not record a valuation allowance for t
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	he period. This determination was
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	based on an estimated forecast of future taxable income which includes many judgments and assumptions. Accordingly, it is at least reasonably possible for future changes in one or more assumptions may lead to a change in judgment regarding the necessity of a valuation allowance required in future periods.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	Our largest deferred tax asset is related to our investment in partnership of $
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	136.1
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	million. This deferred tax asset is a result of the differences between the book and tax basis in Adeptus Health LLC, which is the partnership that operates our facilities.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	A second component of the deferred tax asset is related to the Tax Receivable Agreement (noted below) liability of $
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	65.9
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	million.&nbsp;&nbsp;As the Company becomes profitable, the deferred tax asset related to this liability will be reduced.&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	The final component of the deferred tax asset is the federal net operating loss carryforwards of
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	$4.2
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	million. The federal net operating losses will begin to expire in 2034.&nbsp;&nbsp;The net operating loss carryforward is primarily related to depreciation and amortization deductions
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	. The gross amount of the federal net operating loss carryforward was
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	$12.0
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	million at December 31, 2015.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>

<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;COLOR:#000000;">
	Adeptus Health Inc. and Subsidiaries
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 6PT;TEXT-ALIGN:CENTER;COLOR:#000000;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;COLOR:#000000;">
	NOTES TO CONSOLIDATED FINANCIAL STATEMENTS
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 6PT;TEXT-ALIGN:CENTER;COLOR:#000000;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
	&nbsp;
</P>
</DIV>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="MARGIN-LEFT:10.2941176470588%;MARGIN-RIGHT:10.2941176470588%;">
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	A cumulative change in ownership among material shareholders, as defined in Section 382 of the Internal Revenue Code, during a three-year period may limit the utilization of the federal net operating loss carryforwards. At this time, the Company is not subject to the Section 382 limitation; however the Company may be subject to this limitation depending on the extent and timing of change in ownership in the future.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	Uncertain Tax Positions
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	At December 31, 201
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	5
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	, the Company has not identified or accrued for any uncertain tax positions. Our policy is to include interest and penalties related to uncertain tax positions, and as of December 31, 201
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	5
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	, there were no accrued interest and penalties. We file tax returns in the U.S. federal jurisdiction and state jurisdictions where we have facilities and operations. We are not currently under audit for fed
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	eral or any state jurisdictions; however, our 2011 (Texas only) &#x2013; 2014 tax returns remain open for examination.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;PUNCTUATION-WRAP:HANGING;LINE-HEIGHT:8.9PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	Tax
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	Receivable
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	Agreement
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:2.9PT 5.5PT 12PT 0PT;PUNCTUATION-WRAP:HANGING;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	Upon the consummation of the Company&#x2019;s initial public offering,
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	the Company
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	entered into a tax receivable agreement with the LLC Unit holders after the closing of the offering that provides for the payment from time to time by the Company to the LLC Unit holders of
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	85%
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	of the amount of the benefits, if any, that the Company is deemed to realize as a result of increases in tax basis and certain other tax benefits related to exchanges of LLC Units pursuant to the exchange agreement, including tax benefits attributable to payments under the tax receivable agreement.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	These payment obligations are obligations of the Company
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	; however, payments to LLC Unit holders will only be paid as tax benefits for the Company are realized.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	For purposes of the tax receivable agreement, the benefit deemed realized by the Company was computed by comparing its actual income tax liability (calculated with certain assumptions) to the amount of such taxes that the Company would have been required to pay had there been no increase to the tax basis of the assets of Adeptus Health LLC as a result of the exchanges and had the Company not entered into the tax receivable agreement. The step-up in basis will depend on the fair value of the LLC Units at conversion.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	As of December 31, 201
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	5
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	, the Company has recorded an estimated payable pursuant to the tax receivable agreement of
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	$191.3
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	million related to
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	exchanges of LLC Units
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	in
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	connection
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	with public offering
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	s
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	and other exchanges
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	that are expected to give rise to certain tax benefits in the future.
</FONT>
</P>

</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	.&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:INHERIT;">
	Basic net income (loss) per share is computed by dividing the net income (loss) by the weighted average number of common shares outstanding during the period. Diluted net income (loss) per share is computed by using the weighted average number of common shares outstanding, including potential dilutive shares of common stock assuming the dilutive effect of outstanding stock options and restricted stock
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:INHERIT;">
	using the treasury stock method.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;TEXT-INDENT:24.5PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
</FONT>
</P>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="MARGIN-LEFT:10.2941176470588%;MARGIN-RIGHT:10.2941176470588%;">
<P>
<FONT SIZE="1">
</FONT>
</P>
<DIV STYLE="WIDTH:100%">
<P STYLE="MARGIN:24PT 0PT 0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:CENTER;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	107

</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
