<DIV STYLE="MARGIN-LEFT:10.2941176470588%;MARGIN-RIGHT:10.2941176470588%;">
<EFX_ACCOUNTING_CHANGES>
<A NAME="FIS_ACCOUNTING_CHANGES"></A>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	Item 9. Changes in and Disagreements with Accountant
</FONT>
<A NAME="ADPT-20151231X10K_HTM_ITEM9CHANGESINANDDISAGREEMENTSWITHACCOUN">
</A>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	s on Accounting and Financial Disclosure
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	None
</FONT>
</P>
</EFX_ACCOUNTING_CHANGES>
<EFX_CONTROL_AND_PROCEDURES>
<A NAME="FIS_CONTROL_AND_PROCEDURES"></A>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	Item&nbsp;9A. Controls and Procedures
</FONT>
<A NAME="ADPT-20151231X10K_HTM_ITEM9ACONTROLSANDPROCEDURES_469114">
</A>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:19.8PT 0PT 12PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;COLOR:#000000;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	HIPAA and its implementing regulations establish electronic data transmission standards that all healthcare providers must use for certain electronic healthcare transactions, such as submitting claims for payment for medical services.&nbsp;&nbsp;HIPAA requires the use of standard code sets for certain diagnoses and procedures known as ICD
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209;10 code sets.&nbsp;&nbsp;Use of the ICD
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209;10 code sets was required beginning October&nbsp;1, 2015.&nbsp;&nbsp;During 2015, the Company concluded that it did not have the internal expertise within its current structure to meet the medical record coding and billing compliance requirements under ICD-10.&nbsp;&nbsp;As such, management outsourced these functions to a third-party service provider as of October 1, 2015.&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	The Company&#x2019;s contract with the third-party service provider requires that the third-party service organization provide to the Company, on an annual basis, a Service Organization Control internal control report in accordance with the AICPA Attestation Standards, Section 801,
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;COLOR:#000000;">
	&nbsp;Reporting on Controls at a Service Organization,
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	&nbsp;addressing the suitability of the design and operating effectiveness of controls relating to the system and business processing activities performed by the service organization on the Company&#x2019;s behalf.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&nbsp;The
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	internal control report provided by the service organization
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	was not sufficient for our purposes because it did not specifically address transactions and controls operating from the commencement date of our contract through year end because the scope of the report only covered transactions and controls for the period January 1, 2015 to September 30, 2015,
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	and we did not have other controls in place that were adequate to verify the integrity of the data throughout the process in which patient encounters were coded and billed nor controls over the coding of medical records.&nbsp;&nbsp;Additionally, internal controls designed to ensure the completeness and accuracy of the patient information transferred to the third-party service provider were not effective.&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	As a result, the Company
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	could not conclude that controls over the completeness, existence and accuracy of revenue and accounts receivable were operating effectively.&nbsp;&nbsp;We attempted to implement alternative internal control procedures to verify revenue information received from the third party was complete and accurate; however, we were unable to implement manual controls to compensate for the lack of evidence to support effective controls at our service provider.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:19.8PT 0PT 12PT;COLOR:#000000;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;COLOR:#000000;">
	Evaluation of Disclosure Controls and Procedures
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:6.6PT 0PT 12PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;COLOR:#000000;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	Our management, with the participation of our chief executive officer and chief financial officer, performed an evaluation of our disclosure controls and procedures (as defined in Rules 13a-15(e) and 15d-15(e) under the Exchange Act) as of the end of the period covered by this annual report.&nbsp;&nbsp;Management recognizes that any controls and procedures, no matter how well designed and operated, can provide only reasonable assurance of achieving their objectives, and management necessarily applies its judgment in evaluating the cost-benefit relationship of possible controls and procedures.&nbsp;&nbsp;Our disclosure controls and procedures are designed to provide reasonable assurance of achieving their control objectives.&nbsp;&nbsp;Based on the evaluation of our disclosure controls and procedures as of the end of the period covered by this annual report, our chief executive officer and chief financial officer concluded that, as of such date, our disclosure controls and procedures were not effective at the reasonable assurance level because of a material weakness described below in Management&#x2019;s Report on Internal Control over Financial Reporting.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:19.8PT 0PT 12PT;COLOR:#000000;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;COLOR:#000000;">
	Management&#x2019;s Report on Internal Control over Financial Reporting
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:6.6PT 0PT 12PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;COLOR:#000000;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	Our management is responsible for establishing and maintaining adequate internal control over financial reporting. Internal control over financial reporting is defined in Rules 13a-15(f) and 15d-15(f) promulgated under the Exchange Act as a process designed by, or under the supervision of, the Company&#x2019;s principal executive and principal financial officers and effected by the Company&#x2019;s board of directors, management, and other personnel, to provide reasonable assurance regarding the reliability of financial reporting and the preparation of financial statements for external purposes in accordance with generally accepted accounting principles.&nbsp;&nbsp;Because of its inherent limitations, internal control over financial reporting may not prevent or detect misstatements. Projections of any evaluation of
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
</FONT>
</P>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="MARGIN-LEFT:10.2941176470588%;MARGIN-RIGHT:10.2941176470588%;">
<P>
<FONT SIZE="1">
</FONT>
</P>
<DIV STYLE="WIDTH:100%">
<P STYLE="MARGIN:24PT 0PT 0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:CENTER;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	110
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
</FONT>
</P>
</DIV>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="MARGIN-LEFT:10.2941176470588%;MARGIN-RIGHT:10.2941176470588%;">
<HR ALIGN="CENTER" STYLE='BACKGROUND-COLOR:#000000; BORDER-WIDTH:0; COLOR:#000000; HEIGHT:2PT; LINEHEIGHT:0; WIDTH:100%;'>
</HR>
<P STYLE="PAGE-BREAK-AFTER:ALWAYS">
	&nbsp;
</P>
<A NAME="eolPage111"></A>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="MARGIN-LEFT:10.2941176470588%;MARGIN-RIGHT:10.2941176470588%;">
<DIV STYLE="WIDTH:100%">
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 30PT;COLOR:#0563C1;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<A HREF="#ADPT-20151231X10K_HTM_TOC">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#0563C1;">
	Table of Contents
</FONT>
</A>
</P>
</DIV>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="MARGIN-LEFT:10.2941176470588%;MARGIN-RIGHT:10.2941176470588%;">
<P STYLE="MARGIN:6.6PT 0PT 12PT;COLOR:#000000;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	effectiveness to future periods are subject to the risk that controls may become inadequate because of changes in conditions, or that the degree of compliance with the policies or procedures may deteriorate.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:13.2PT 0PT 12PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;COLOR:#000000;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	Our management assessed the effectiveness of our internal control over financial reporting as of December 31, 2015. In making this assessment, our management used the criteria set forth in
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;COLOR:#000000;">
	Internal Control-Integrated Framework (2013)
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	issued by the Committee of Sponsoring Organizations of the Treadway Commission (COSO). Based on its assessment, our management has determined that due to the material weakness described below, our internal control over financial reporting was not effective as of December 31, 2015.&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:13.2PT 0PT 12PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;COLOR:#000000;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	The Company&#x2019;s risk assessment process failed to design and implement appropriate process level and monitoring controls over revenue billing transactions and related accounts receivable performed by a third-party service provider on our behalf as of December 31, 2015.&nbsp;&nbsp;Additionally, the Company&#x2019;s internal control activities designed to ensure revenue transaction data being transferred to the third-party service provider is complete and accurate were not operating effectively as of December 31, 2015.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:13.2PT 0PT 12PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;COLOR:#000000;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	Although no adjustment was required to our consolidated financial statements, management concluded that there is a reasonable possibility that a material misstatement could occur in revenue and related receivables in the consolidated financial statements if the control deficiencies were not remediated.&nbsp;&nbsp;Accordingly, management concluded that there is a material weakness in the Company&#x2019;s internal control over financial reporting and that the Company did not maintain effective internal control over financial reporting as of December 31, 2015.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:13.2PT 0PT 12PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;COLOR:#000000;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	KPMG LLP has issued an adverse report on the effectiveness of our internal control over financial reporting. This report is included in the Reports of Independent Registered Public Accounting Firms in Item 15.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:19.8PT 0PT 12PT;COLOR:#000000;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;COLOR:#000000;">
	Planned Remediation of Material Weakness
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:6.6PT 0PT 12PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;COLOR:#000000;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	The third-party service provider is used by the Company to code claims and bill payors using ICD-10 code sets.&nbsp;&nbsp;As of December 31, 2015, the internal control report provided by the service organization in assessing the effectiveness of its internal control over financial reporting was not sufficient for our purposes since the scope of the report did not include our transactions and data in the environment that was subject to the audit.&nbsp;&nbsp;To address this issue, the Company plans to obtain an appropriate internal control report from the service organization to meet its reporting needs for the year ended December 31, 2016.&nbsp;&nbsp;Additionally, the Company will implement appropriate controls over the completeness and accuracy of revenue transaction data exchanged with the third-party service provider.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:6.6PT 0PT 12PT;COLOR:#000000;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	C
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;COLOR:#000000;">
	hanges in Internal Control over Financial Reporting
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:6.6PT 0PT 12PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;COLOR:#000000;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	Other than the controls related to the material weakness described above, there were no changes in our internal control over financial reporting (as defined in Rule 13a-15(d) under the Exchange Act) that occurred during the quarter ended December 31, 2015 that have materially affected, or are reasonably likely to materially affect, our internal control over financial reporting.
</FONT>
</P>
</EFX_CONTROL_AND_PROCEDURES>

<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	Item 9B. Other Informatio

	n

	None

<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 8PT;TEXT-ALIGN:RIGHT;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;LINE-HEIGHT:107.92%;FONT-SIZE: 12PT;">
<A NAME="ADPT-20151231EX231ECE74E_HTM__GOBACK">
</A>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE:12PT;">
	Exhibit 23.1
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 8PT;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;LINE-HEIGHT:107.92%;FONT-SIZE: 12PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:12PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<EFX_EXPERTS_CONSENT>
<A NAME="FIS_EXPERTS_CONSENT"></A>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 3PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;TEXT-INDENT:0.25PT;TEXT-ALIGN:CENTER;COLOR:#000000;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-SIZE: 12PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;COLOR:#000000;FONT-SIZE:12PT;">
	Consent of Independent Registered Public Accounting Firm
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 8PT;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;LINE-HEIGHT:107.92%;FONT-SIZE: 12PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:12PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 3PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;TEXT-INDENT:0.25PT;COLOR:#000000;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-SIZE: 12PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;COLOR:#000000;FONT-SIZE:12PT;">
	The Board of Directors
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 8PT;COLOR:#000000;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;LINE-HEIGHT:107.92%;FONT-SIZE: 12PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;COLOR:#000000;FONT-SIZE:12PT;">
	Adeptus Health Inc.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;COLOR:#000000;FONT-SIZE:12PT;">
	and subsidiaries
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;COLOR:#000000;FONT-SIZE:12PT;">
	:
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 10PT;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 12PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:12PT;">
	We consent to the incorporation by reference in the registration statement (No. 333-196997) on Form S-8 of Adeptus Health Inc. and subsidiaries of our report dated February 29, 2016, with respect to the consolidated balance sheets of Adeptus Health Inc. and subsidiaries as of December&nbsp;31, 2015 and 2014, and the related consolidated statements of operations, comprehensive income (loss), changes in shareholders&#x2019;/owners&#x2019; equity, and cash flows for each of the years in the three-year period ended December&nbsp;31, 2015,
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;FONT-SIZE:12PT;">
	and the effectiveness of internal control over financial reporting as of December 31, 2015,
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:12PT;">
	which reports appear in the December&nbsp;31, 2015 annual report on Form 10-K of Adeptus Health Inc. and subsidiaries.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 10PT;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;COLOR:#000000;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 12PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;FONT-SIZE:12PT;">
	Our report dated February 29, 2016, on the effectiveness of internal control over financial reporting as of December 31, 2015, expresses our opinion that Adeptus Health Inc. (the Company) did not maintain effective internal control over financial reporting as of December 31, 2015 because of the effect of a material weakness on the achievement of the objectives of the control criteria and contains an explanatory paragraph that states the Company&#x2019;s risk assessment process failed to design and implement appropriate process level and monitoring controls over revenue billing transactions and related accounts receivable performed by a third-party service provider on their behalf and internal control activities designed to ensure revenue transaction data being transferred to the third-party service provider is complete and accurate.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:12PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 8PT;COLOR:#000000;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;LINE-HEIGHT:107.92%;FONT-SIZE: 12PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:12PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 8PT;COLOR:#000000;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;LINE-HEIGHT:107.92%;FONT-SIZE: 12PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;COLOR:#000000;FONT-SIZE:12PT;">
	/s/ KPMG LLP
</FONT>
